'''Demetria Devonne''' "'''Demi'''" ''' Lovato''' ({{IPAc-en|'|d|ɛ|m|i|_|l|ə|ˈ|v|ɑː|t|oʊ}} {{respell|DEM|ee|_|lə|VAH|toh}};<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ICAa3s8eVDA&t=5s|title=Demi Lovato Talks Favorite Dishes, Poot, and the Rock Version of "Sorry Not Sorry"|date=July 14, 2023 |time=0:05 |url-status=live |author=Harper's BAZAAR|via=YouTube|archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/ICAa3s8eVDA|archive-date=December 22, 2023}}{{cbignore}}</ref> born August 20, 1992) is an American singer, songwriter, and actress. After appearing on the children's television series ''[[Barney & Friends]]'' (2002–2004), she{{Efn|Lovato uses both [[She (pronoun)|she/her]] and [[Singular they|they/them]] pronouns. This article uses she/her pronouns for consistency.|name=pronouns|group=lower-alpha}} starred in the [[Disney Channel]] short series ''[[As the Bell Rings (American TV series)|As the Bell Rings]]'' (2007–2008). Lovato rose to prominence for playing Mitchie Torres in the musical television film ''[[Camp Rock]]'' (2008) and its sequel ''[[Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam]]'' (2010). The former film's [[Camp Rock (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] contained "[[This Is Me (Demi Lovato song)|This Is Me]]", her debut single and duet, which peaked at number nine on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].

After signing with [[Hollywood Records]], Lovato released her [[pop rock]] debut album, ''[[Don't Forget]]'' (2008), which debuted at number two on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]. Its follow-up, ''[[Here We Go Again (Demi Lovato album)|Here We Go Again]]'' (2009), debuted at number one in the US, while its [[Here We Go Again (Demi Lovato song)|title track]] reached number 15 on the Hot 100. Her third studio album, ''[[Unbroken (Demi Lovato album)|Unbroken]]'' (2011), experimented with [[Pop music|pop]] and [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]], and spawned the US top-ten single "[[Skyscraper (song)|Skyscraper]]". She released her self-titled [[Demi (album)|fourth album]] in 2013, which debuted at number three on the ''Billboard'' 200, and contained the international top-ten song "[[Heart Attack (Demi Lovato song)|Heart Attack]]". Lovato's fifth and sixth albums, ''[[Confident (album)|Confident]]'' (2015) and ''[[Tell Me You Love Me (album)|Tell Me You Love Me]]'' (2017), infused [[Soul music|soul]] and mature themes. She earned a [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album|Grammy Award]] nomination for ''Confident'', while "[[Sorry Not Sorry (Demi Lovato song)|Sorry Not Sorry]]", the lead single from ''Tell Me You Love Me'', became her highest-charting single in the US, reaching number six. After a hiatus, she released her seventh and eighth albums ''[[Dancing with the Devil... the Art of Starting Over]]'' (2021) and ''[[Holy Fvck]]'' (2022), which respectively reached numbers two and seven in the US; the latter marked a return to rock-influenced music.

On television, Lovato starred as the titular character on the sitcom ''[[Sonny with a Chance]]'' (2009–2011), served as a judge on the music competition series ''[[The X Factor (American TV series)|The X Factor USA]]'' for its [[The X Factor (American TV series) season 2|second]] and [[The X Factor (American TV series) season 3|third]] seasons (2012–2013), appeared as a recurring character on the musical comedy ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' (2013–2014) and the sitcom ''[[Will & Grace]]'' (2020), and hosted her [[The Demi Lovato Show|self-titled talk show]] and the docuseries ''Unidentified with Demi Lovato'' (both 2021). She also starred in the television drama film ''[[Princess Protection Program]]'' (2009), the animated films ''[[Smurfs: The Lost Village]]'' (2017) and [[Charming (film)|''Charming'']] (2018), the musical comedy ''[[Eurovision Song Contest: The Story of Fire Saga]]'' (2020), and the documentary ''[[Child Star (film)|Child Star]]'' (2024); the last of which she also co-directed. 

Lovato has sold over 24 million records in the United States and has also received numerous [[List of awards and nominations received by Demi Lovato|accolades]], including an [[MTV Video Music Award]], 14 [[Teen Choice Awards]], five [[People's Choice Awards]], two [[Latin American Music Awards]], and a ''[[Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record]]''; she was included on the [[Time 100|''Time'' 100]] annual list in 2017. She co-founded the former record label [[Safehouse Records]], under [[Universal Music Group]], with singer [[Nick Jonas]] in 2015. An activist for various social causes, Lovato's struggles with an eating disorder and [[substance abuse]] have received considerable media attention, in response to which she published the [[Self-help book|self-help]] memoir ''Staying Strong: 365 Days a Year'' (2013) and released the documentaries ''[[Demi Lovato: Stay Strong]]'' (2012), ''[[Demi Lovato: Simply Complicated]]'' (2017), and ''[[Demi Lovato: Dancing with the Devil]]'' (2021).

==Early life and career beginnings==
Demetria Devonne Lovato was born on August 20, 1992, in [[Albuquerque, New Mexico]],<!--SEE TALK BEFORE CHANGING TO DALLAS --><ref name="BioChannelBiography">{{cite web|url=https://www.biography.com/musician/demi-lovato|title=Demi Lovato|date=June 14, 2021|publisher=Biography|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=April 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415172913/https://www.biography.com/people/demi-lovato-481444|url-status=live}}</ref> to former [[Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders|Dallas Cowboys cheerleader]] Dianna De La Garza (née Lee Smith)<ref name=MotherLine>{{cite web|title=Sue Emmons and Donald Smith|url=http://familytreemaker.genealogy.com/users/h/a/r/Sue-D-Hart-Ar/GENE3-0008.html|publisher=Family Tree Maker|access-date=February 17, 2014|archive-date=October 15, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141015103853/http://familytreemaker.genealogy.com/users/h/a/r/Sue-D-Hart-Ar/GENE3-0008.html|url-status=live}}</ref> and engineer and musician Patrick Martin Lovato.<ref name=PatrickDeathBillboard>{{cite magazine|last=Payne|first=Chris|title=Demi Lovato's Father Dies|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovatos-father-passes-away-1568025/|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304081941/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovatos-father-passes-away-1568025/|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato has an older full sister named Dallas,<ref name="DallasBirthday">{{cite web|title=Happy 24th Birthday Dallas Lovato February 4, 2012 |url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2012/02/04/happy-24th-birthday-dallas-lovato-february-4-2012/ |publisher=Disney Dreaming |access-date=February 4, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120208061154/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2012/02/04/happy-24th-birthday-dallas-lovato-february-4-2012/ |archive-date=February 8, 2012 }}</ref> a younger maternal half-sister, actress [[Madison De La Garza]],<ref name="WP">{{cite news|first=Laura|last=Yao|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/06/20/AR2008062003077_pf.html|title=Disney Demi-Goddess|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|date=June 21, 2008|access-date=March 11, 2013|archive-date=June 29, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629025242/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/06/20/AR2008062003077_pf.html|url-status=live}}</ref> and an older paternal half-sister, Amber, whom Lovato first spoke to at age 20.<ref name="amber-lovato">{{cite magazine|title=Demi Lovato Reveals Secret Half-Sister|url=https://people.com/celebrity/demi-lovato-has-a-30-year-old-half-sister/|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=March 6, 2013|access-date=April 3, 2017|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170404013116/http://people.com/celebrity/demi-lovato-has-a-30-year-old-half-sister/|archive-date=April 4, 2017}}</ref>

In mid-1994, shortly after Lovato's second birthday, her parents divorced.<ref name=Chance>{{cite book|first=Jody|last=Jensen Shaffer|title=Demi Lovato: Taking Another Chance|year=2013|publisher=Lerner Publications|location=Minneapolis, Minnesota|isbn=978-1467715515|page=7}}</ref> Her father was of [[Hispanos of New Mexico|Nuevomexicano]] descent, with mostly Spanish and [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]] ancestors, and came from a family that had been living in New Mexico for generations; he also had distant Portuguese and [[Jews|Jewish]] ancestry.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5xMrNnZ21Ck |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211221/5xMrNnZ21Ck |archive-date=December 21, 2021 |url-status=live|title=Demi Lovato finds out she's Jewish!?|last=KISS FM UK|date=September 22, 2015|access-date=March 10, 2017|via=YouTube}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref name="Hispanic Hollywood">{{cite news|title=The Young Hispanic Hollywood Class of 2013|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/young-hispanic-hollywood-class-2013-658782/|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date=March 4, 2022|date=November 22, 2013|quote=In honor of her Mexican-American father,|archive-date=March 14, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140314151249/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/demi-lovato-658894|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was a descendant of [[American Civil War|Civil War]] [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]] veteran [[Francisco Perea]] and [[Santa Fe de Nuevo México]] governor [[Francisco Xavier Chávez]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.somosprimos.com/sp2010/spjun10/spjun10.htm|title=Somos Primos|publisher=Diario El Carabobeño|access-date=October 5, 2013|archive-date=September 15, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180915193007/http://www.somosprimos.com/sp2010/spjun10/spjun10.htm|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato had no interest in forging a relationship with Patrick after her parents divorced.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hoyle|first=Antonia|date=April 22, 2012|title=The fame, the drugs, the self-harm|url=http://fabulousmag.co.uk/2012/04/22/the-fame-the-drugs-the-self-harm/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121101094046/http://fabulousmag.co.uk/2012/04/22/the-fame-the-drugs-the-self-harm/|archive-date=November 1, 2012|access-date=March 16, 2013|website=Fabulous}}</ref> Her mother is of Irish descent.<ref>{{cite web|first=Nicola|last=Murphy|url=https://www.irishcentral.com/culture/entertainment/how-irish-ancestry-links-demi-lovato-megan-fox-and-olivia-wilde-photos-213964591-237761091|title=How Irish ancestry links Demi Lovato, Megan Fox and Olivia Wilde|website=Irish Central|date=March 15, 2014|access-date=August 26, 2015|archive-date=April 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415173414/https://www.irishcentral.com/culture/entertainment/how-irish-ancestry-links-demi-lovato-megan-fox-and-olivia-wilde-photos-213964591-237761091|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=ddlovato|number=267890338557992960|title= actually - I found out that I am Irish, Hispanic, Native American, Portuguese and Jewish!!!|first=Demi|last=Lovato|access-date=March 4, 2022}}</ref>

She has been vocal about her strained relationship with her father, calling him abusive and once stated, "He was mean, but he wanted to be a good person. And he wanted to have his family, and when my mom married my stepdad, he still had this huge heart where he said, 'I'm so glad that [he's] taking care of you and doing the job that I wish I could do.'"<ref>{{cite web|last=Bueno|first=Antoinette|date=October 20, 2015|title=Demi Lovato Opens Up About Her 'Abusive' Father: 'I Was Very Conflicted When He Passed'|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/174362_demi_lovato_opens_up_about_her_abusive_father_patrick_lovato/|access-date=February 27, 2017|work=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|archive-date=March 17, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230317123647/https://www.etonline.com/news/174362_demi_lovato_opens_up_about_her_abusive_father_patrick_lovato|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=October 22, 2015|title=Demi Lovato talks about her relationship with her father|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/demi-lovato-talks-about-her-relationship-with-her-father|access-date=March 4, 2022|publisher=[[Fox News]]|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304081934/https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/demi-lovato-talks-about-her-relationship-with-her-father|url-status=live}}</ref> After Patrick died of cancer on June 22, 2013,<ref name="Cover">{{cite news|date=June 27, 2013|title=Demi Lovato speaks on dad's death|publisher=[[CNN]]|url=http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/27/showbiz/celebrity-news-gossip/demi-lovato-father-mental-illness|access-date=June 28, 2013|archive-date=March 12, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210312035327/https://www.cnn.com/2013/06/27/showbiz/celebrity-news-gossip/demi-lovato-father-mental-illness|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato said that he had been mentally ill, and she created the Lovato Treatment Scholarship Program in his honor.<ref name="Lovece">{{cite news|last=Lovece|first=Frank|date=June 27, 2013|title=Demi Lovato discusses father's death on 'Good Morning America'|work=Newsday|url=http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/celebrities/demi-lovato-discusses-father-s-death-on-good-morning-america-1.5583327|access-date=June 28, 2013|archive-date=March 12, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210312035332/https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/celebrities/demi-lovato-discusses-father-s-death-on-good-morning-america-1.5583327|url-status=live}}</ref>

Lovato was brought up in [[Dallas]], Texas.<ref name="Biography Today">{{cite book|title=Biography Today|year=2009|page=[https://archive.org/details/biographytodaypr0000unse/page/103 103]|publisher=Omnigraphics|location=Detroit, Michigan|isbn=978-0-7808-1052-5|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/biographytodaypr0000unse/page/103}}</ref><ref name="ref091">{{cite news|first=Jon|last=Caramanica|title=Tween Princess, Tweaked|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=July 15, 2009|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/19/arts/music/19cara.html|access-date=November 4, 2009|archive-date=July 21, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090721030658/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/19/arts/music/19cara.html|url-status=live}}</ref> She began playing the piano at age seven and guitar at 10,<ref>"Biography Today", p.105.</ref> when she began dancing and acting classes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/videos/this-is-how-i-made-it-ep-6-demi-lovato-and-bob/1698279/playlist.jhtml|title=Demi Lovato and B.o.B.|website=[[MTV]]|date=December 18, 2012|agency=[[MTV]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141115114500/http://www.mtv.com/videos/this-is-how-i-made-it-ep-6-demi-lovato-and-bob/1698279/playlist.jhtml|archive-date=November 15, 2014|url-status=dead|access-date=March 7, 2013}}</ref> In 2002, Lovato began her acting career on the children's television series ''[[Barney & Friends]]'', portraying the role of Angela.<ref name="Barney">{{cite web|last=Bryson|first=Carey|title=Demi Lovato The Disney Star Machine Does It Again|url=http://kidstvmovies.about.com/od/camprock/a/demilovato.htm|access-date=March 11, 2013|agency=[[Dotdash]]|archive-date=May 26, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526215857/http://kidstvmovies.about.com/od/camprock/a/demilovato.htm|url-status=dead}}</ref> She appeared on ''[[Prison Break]]'' in 2006 and on ''[[Just Jordan]]'' the following year.<ref name="BioChannelBiography" /> Due to her acting career, Lovato was bullied and consequently requested [[homeschooling]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Culbertson|first=Caroline|date=November 2, 2010|title=Demi Lovato in rehab: Dad blames Hollywood, acting for her issues|newspaper=[[New York Daily News]]|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/demi-lovato-rehab-dad-blames-hollywood-acting-issues-article-1.451886|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=April 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415172920/https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/demi-lovato-rehab-dad-blames-hollywood-acting-issues-article-1.451886|url-status=live}}</ref> through which she eventually received her high-school diploma.<ref>{{cite web|date=April 23, 2009|title=Demi Lovato Graduates High School|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2009/04/23/demi-lovato-graduates-high-school/|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100407010117/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2009/04/23/demi-lovato-graduates-high-school/|archive-date=April 7, 2010|access-date=July 27, 2011|website=Disney Dreaming}}</ref>

==Career==
===2007–2008: Breakthrough with ''Camp Rock'' and ''Don't Forget''===
[[File:Demi Lovato Crop.jpg|left|thumb|upright|Lovato in [[London]] in September 2008]]
From 2007 to 2008, Lovato played Charlotte Adams on the [[Disney Channel]] short series ''[[As the Bell Rings (U.S. TV series)|As the Bell Rings]]''.<ref name=AboutDemi>{{cite web|title=About Demi Lovato|url=http://demilovatotour.com/html/about_demi_lovato.html|publisher=demilovatotour.com|access-date=September 13, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104011501/http://demilovatotour.com/html/about_demi_lovato.html |archive-date=November 4, 2013}}</ref> Lovato auditioned for the channel's television film ''[[Camp Rock]]'' and series ''[[Sonny with a Chance]]'' during 2007 and got both roles.<ref name="Victoria">{{cite news|url=http://www.victoriaadvocate.com/news/2009/jun/22/bc-mus-demilovatoaa-_-entertainment/?entertainment&national-entertainment|title=Disney singing sensation Demi Lovato ready for new album, first tour as headliner|first=John J.|last=Moser|work=[[The Victoria Advocate]]|publisher=Victoria Advocate Publishing Co.|date=June 22, 2009|access-date=March 11, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130818042131/http://www.victoriaadvocate.com/news/2009/jun/22/bc-mus-demilovatoaa-_-entertainment/?entertainment&national-entertainment|archive-date=August 18, 2013}}</ref> Lovato played the lead character, aspiring singer Mitchie Torres, in ''Camp Rock''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kidstvmovies.about.com/od/camprock/fr/camprockr.htm|title=Camp Rock (2008) – Movie Review for Parents|first=Carey|last=Bryson|website=[[About.com]]|publisher=[[IAC (company)|IAC]]|location=New York City|access-date=March 11, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130421105530/http://kidstvmovies.about.com/od/camprock/fr/camprockr.htm|archive-date=April 21, 2013}}</ref> The film premiered on June 20, 2008, to 8.9&nbsp;million viewers.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/showtracker/2008/06/high-ratings-fo.html|title=High ratings for 'Camp Rock,' the Disney Channel's Jonas Brothers movie|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=June 21, 2008|access-date=March 11, 2013|archive-date=May 21, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220521194702/https://latimesblogs.latimes.com/showtracker/2008/06/high-ratings-fo.html|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Gillian Flynn]] of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' wrote that Lovato's acting skills were underwhelming and that she has "the knee-jerk smile of someone who is often told she has a great smile".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/article/2008/06/13/camp-rock/|title=Camp Rock (2008)|first=Gillian|last=Flynn|author-link=Gillian Flynn|date=June 20, 2008|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=November 26, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221126183705/https://ew.com/article/2008/06/13/camp-rock/|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Camp Rock (soundtrack)|The film's soundtrack]] was released three days earlier; however, the music was considered less current than that of ''[[High School Musical]]''.<ref name="Hinkley">{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/camp-rock-rock-steady-disney-hit-article-1.293920|title='Camp Rock' is a rock-steady Disney hit|first=David|last=Hinkley|work=[[New York Daily News]]|date=June 18, 2008|access-date=June 1, 2013|archive-date=December 1, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221201150213/https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/camp-rock-rock-steady-disney-hit-article-1.293920|url-status=live}}</ref> It debuted at number three on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], with 188,000 units sold in its first week of release.<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Katey|last=Hasty|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/coldplay-cruises-to-no-1-on-the-billboard-200-1044979/|title=Coldplay Cruises To No. 1 On The Billboard 200|magazine=Billboard|date=June 25, 2008|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304081940/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/coldplay-cruises-to-no-1-on-the-billboard-200-1044979/|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato sang four songs on the soundtrack, including "[[We Rock (Camp Rock song)|We Rock]]" and "[[This Is Me (Demi Lovato song)|This Is Me]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0017LFKMO|title=Camp Rock: Original Television Soundtrack: Music|website=Amazon|access-date=March 11, 2013|archive-date=January 10, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160110215437/http://www.amazon.com/dp/B0017LFKMO|url-status=live}}</ref> The latter, Lovato's debut single, debuted at number 11 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and later peaked at number nine, marking her first entry on the chart.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100|title=Top 100 Songs {{!}} Billboard Hot 100 Chart|magazine=Billboard|access-date=May 11, 2019|archive-date=October 27, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211027024922/https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100|url-status=live}}</ref> That summer, Lovato signed with [[Hollywood Records]] and began her Demi Live! Warm Up Tour before the release of her debut studio album,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ovguide.com/demi-live!-warm-up-tour-9202a8c04000641f800000000879c65e|title=Demi Live! Warm Up Tour Video|publisher=OVGuide|access-date=March 11, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022024108/http://www.ovguide.com/demi-live!-warm-up-tour-9202a8c04000641f800000000879c65e|archive-date=October 22, 2013}}</ref> and appeared on the [[Jonas Brothers]]' [[Burnin' Up Tour]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zvents.com/essex_junction_vt/events/show/83554500-jonas-brothers-the-burning-up-tour-with-special-guest-demi-lovato |title=Jonas Brothers: The Burning Up Tour with special guest Demi Lovato |publisher=Zvents |access-date=March 11, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103200933/http://www.zvents.com/essex_junction_vt/events/show/83554500-jonas-brothers-the-burning-up-tour-with-special-guest-demi-lovato |archive-date=November 3, 2013 }}</ref>

Lovato's debut studio album, ''[[Don't Forget]]'', released on September 23, 2008, was met with generally positive reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.absolutepunk.net/showthread.php?t=1279002|title=Demi Lovato – Don't Forget|work=AbsolutePunk.net|access-date=August 26, 2015|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120716221811/http://www.absolutepunk.net/showthread.php?t=1279002|archive-date=July 16, 2012}}</ref><ref name="DigitalSpy">{{cite news|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/music/album-reviews/a154015/demi-lovato-dont-forget/|title=Demi Lovato: 'Don't Forget'|date=April 20, 2009|last=Levine|first=Nick|work=[[Digital Spy]]|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150405/https://www.digitalspy.com/music/album-reviews/a154015/demi-lovato-dont-forget/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Allmusic">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/here-we-go-again-r2278939/review|title=Here We Go Again – Demi Lovato|work=[[AllMusic]]|publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]]|location=San Carlos, California|last=Erlewine|first=Stephen Thomas|access-date=October 9, 2011|archive-date=March 5, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240305125612/https://www.allmusic.com/album/here-we-go-again-mw0000822778/trackListingAjax|url-status=live}}</ref> Michael Slezak of ''Entertainment Weekly'' said, "Demi Lovato might satisfy her 'tween fans but she won't be winning any rockers over with ''Don't Forget''".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/article/2008/09/17/dont-forget/|title=Don't Forget|first=Michael|last=Slezak|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=September 17, 2008|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305234901/https://ew.com/article/2008/09/17/dont-forget/|url-status=live}}</ref> The album debuted at number two in the US, with first-week sales of 89,000 copies.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/on-the-charts-demi-lovato-kings-of-leon-debut-high-metallica-rule-102719/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081004053422/http://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2008/10/01/on-the-charts-demi-lovato-kings-of-leon-debut-high-metallica-rule/|title=On the Charts: Demi Lovato & Kings of Leon Debut High, Metallica Rule|first=Daniel|last=Kreps|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=October 1, 2008|archive-date=October 4, 2008|access-date=March 4, 2022}}</ref> Ten of its songs were co-written with the Jonas Brothers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/music-jonas-dc-idUSN1541696620080615|title=Jonas Brothers thrilling tweens|first=Amy|last=Donahue|work=[[Reuters]]|publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]]|location=London, England|date=June 25, 2008|access-date=July 7, 2011|archive-date=December 21, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151221234223/http://www.reuters.com/article/music-jonas-dc-idUSN1541696620080615|url-status=live}}</ref>

''Don't Forget'' was certified gold by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) for US sales of over 500,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=Demi+Lovato&ti=don%27t+forget&lab=&genre=&format=&date_option=release&from=&to=&award=&type=&category=&adv=SEARCH#search_section|title=Don't Forget|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|access-date=March 18, 2017|archive-date=May 27, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230527203902/https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=Demi+Lovato&ti=don%27t+forget&lab=&genre=&format=&date_option=release&from=&to=&award=&type=&category=&adv=SEARCH#search_section|url-status=live}}</ref> Its lead single, "[[Get Back (Demi Lovato song)|Get Back]]", was praised for its [[pop rock]] style and peaked at number 43 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Hot 100, also selling over 560,000 copies in the United States.<ref name="billboard.com">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/ask-billboard-songs-two-good-not-to-be-no-1-474115/|title=Ask Billboard: Songs Two Good Not To Be No. 1|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 4, 2022|date=November 17, 2012|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304081935/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/ask-billboard-songs-two-good-not-to-be-no-1-474115/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://archive.boston.com/ae/music/cd_reviews/articles/2008/09/23/at_sweet_16_lovatos_ready_for_her_close_up/ |title=At sweet 16, Lovato's ready for her close-up |newspaper=[[The Boston Globe]] |publisher=Boston Globe Media Partners, L.P. |location=Boston, Massachusetts |date=September 23, 2008 |access-date=March 4, 2022 |archive-date=March 4, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304081937/http://archive.boston.com/ae/music/cd_reviews/articles/2008/09/23/at_sweet_16_lovatos_ready_for_her_close_up/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="BillboardChartHistory">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/demi-lovato/chart-history/|title=Demi Lovato – Chart History|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 11, 2013|archive-date=November 21, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211121094938/https://www.billboard.com/artist/demi-lovato/chart-history/|url-status=live}}</ref> The album's second single, "[[La La Land (Demi Lovato song)|La La Land]]", was cited for its strong rock elements<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/legacy/chartblog/2009/05/demi_lovato_la_la_land.shtml|title=Demi Lovato – 'La La Land'|first=Fraser|last=McAlpine|publisher=[[BBC Music]]. [[BBC]]|date=May 31, 2009|access-date=June 1, 2013|archive-date=July 2, 2014|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140702050632/http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/legacy/chartblog/2009/05/demi_lovato_la_la_land.shtml|url-status=live}}</ref> and peaked at number 52 in the US,<ref name="BillboardChartHistory"/> and cracked the top 40 in Ireland and the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2009&year=2009&week=18|title=Chart Track|publisher=[[Irish Singles Chart]]|access-date=July 26, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120516115853/http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2009&year=2009&week=18|archive-date=May 16, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/La%20La%20Land|title=Demi Lovato – La La Land|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|access-date=July 26, 2011|archive-date=June 11, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150611072907/http://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/la%20la%20land/|url-status=live}}</ref> The music video for the song was directed by [[The Malloys|Brendan Malloy]] and Tim Wheeler.<ref name="Video">{{cite AV media| people= Demi Lovato, Brendan Malloy, Tim Wheeler| title = Making the Video: La La Land| medium = DVD| publisher =Don't Forget (Deluxe Edition)}}</ref>{{full citation needed|date=March 2019}} The third single<ref name="Don'tForget">Sources concerning the single release of "Don't Forget":
*{{cite magazine |title=''Billboard'' |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QdKeU1ZYfwsC |magazine=Billboard |access-date=April 11, 2021 |date=April 25, 2009 |archive-date=March 5, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240305125512/https://books.google.com/books?id=QdKeU1ZYfwsC |url-status=live }}
*{{cite book |last=Burlingame |first=Jeff |title=Demi!: Latina Star Demi Lovato (Sizzling Celebrities) |date=September 1, 2013 |publisher=[[Enslow Publishing]] |page=25 |quote=''Don't Forget''{{'}}s songs included popular singles 'Get Back,' and 'Don't Forget'.}}</ref> and title track, "[[Don't Forget (Demi Lovato song)|Don't Forget]]", peaked at number 41 in the US.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/demi-lovato|title=Demi Lovato Chart History|magazine=Billboard|access-date=June 1, 2019|archive-date=November 9, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211109103938/https://www.billboard.com/music/Demi-Lovato|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2009–2010: ''Sonny with a Chance'' and ''Here We Go Again''===
Lovato's Disney Channel sitcom ''[[Sonny with a Chance]]'', in which she played Sonny Munroe, the newest cast member of the [[show-within-a-show]] ''So Random!'', premiered on February 8.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/sonny-with-a-chance-season-1/id303224140|title=Sonny With a Chance, Season 1|date=February 7, 2009|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple Inc|access-date=March 11, 2013|archive-date=July 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712124154/https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/sonny-with-a-chance-season-1/id303224140|url-status=live}}</ref> Robert Lloyd of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' described Lovato's acting ability as "very good", comparing her favorably to ''[[Hannah Montana]]'' star [[Miley Cyrus]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2009-feb-06-et-sonny6-story.html |title='Sonny' tests the tween climate |first=Robert |last=Lloyd |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=February 6, 2009 |access-date=March 4, 2022 |archive-date=November 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129075407/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2009-feb-06-et-sonny6-story.html |url-status=live }}</ref> That June, Lovato starred as Rosie Gonzalez / Princess Rosalinda in the Disney Channel film ''[[Princess Protection Program]]'', alongside [[Selena Gomez]]. The film, the fourth highest-rated Disney Channel original movie, premiered to 8.5&nbsp;million viewers.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://blogs.mcall.com/tvwatchers/2009/07/jon-kate-divorce-episode-bet-jackson-tribute-draw-record-audiences.html |title=Jon & Kate divorce episode/ BET Jackson tribute draw record audiences |first=Kathy |last=Lauer-Williams |newspaper=[[The Morning Call]] |publisher=[[Tribune Company]] |location=[[Allentown, Pennsylvania]] |date=July 1, 2009 |access-date=March 4, 2022 |archive-date=August 3, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150406/https://blogs.mcall.com/tvwatchers/2009/07/jon-kate-divorce-episode-bet-jackson-tribute-draw-record-audiences.html |url-status=live }}</ref> For the film's soundtrack, the pair recorded the song "One and the Same", which was later released as a promotional single.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://yaay.today/music/Selena-Gomez-and-Demi-Lovatos-18-year-long-friendship-20200916-0009.html |title=Selena Gomez and Demi Lovato's 18 year-long friendship |publisher=Yaay |date=September 16, 2020 |access-date=October 22, 2020 |archive-date=December 28, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211228173004/https://yaay.today/music/Selena-Gomez-and-Demi-Lovatos-18-year-long-friendship-20200916-0009.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

[[File:DemiLovatoSep10 4.jpg|thumb|upright|Lovato performing on the [[List of Jonas Brothers concert tours#Live in Concert|Jonas Brothers: Live in Concert]] tour in September 2010]]
Lovato's second studio album, ''[[Here We Go Again (Demi Lovato album)|Here We Go Again]]'', was released on July 21, 2009;<ref name="BioChannelBiography"/> she described its acoustic style as similar to that of [[John Mayer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarslam.com/demi-lovato-on-second-album/|title=Demi Lovato on second album|author=Chelsea|date=January 28, 2009|publisher=Sugar Slam|access-date=June 13, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090604140130/http://www.sugarslam.com/demi-lovato-on-second-album/|archive-date=June 4, 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album received favorable reviews from critics who appreciated its enjoyable pop-rock elements, echoing reviews of ''Don't Forget''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/here-we-go-again/demi-lovato|title=Here We Go Again (2009): Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|location=Chicago, Illinois|access-date=July 27, 2011|archive-date=October 23, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023065458/http://www.metacritic.com/music/here-we-go-again/demi-lovato|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato's first number-one album, it debuted atop the ''Billboard'' 200 with first-week sales of 108,000 copies, and was later certified Gold.<ref name="Here We Go Again billboard 200">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-debuts-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-but-michael-jackson-still-reigns-267911/|title=Demi Lovato Debuts At No. 1 On Billboard 200, But Michael Jackson Still Reigns|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|magazine=Billboard|date=July 29, 2009|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304081939/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-debuts-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-but-michael-jackson-still-reigns-267911/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Gold & Platinum">{{cite web |url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=demi+lovato#search_section |title=Gold & Platinum: Demi Lovato |publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]] |access-date=January 19, 2023 |archive-date=May 29, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160529160226/http://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=Demi+Lovato#search_section |url-status=live }}</ref> The album's lead single and title track, "[[Here We Go Again (Demi Lovato song)|Here We Go Again]]", debuted at number 59 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, and managed to peak at number 15, becoming Lovato's highest-charting solo single to that point.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/demi-lovato/chart-history/|title=Demi Lovato Album & Song Chart History – Hot 100|magazine=Billboard|access-date=October 9, 2011|archive-date=November 21, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211121094938/https://www.billboard.com/artist/demi-lovato/chart-history/|url-status=live}}</ref> The song also peaked at number 68 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] and number 38 in New Zealand.<ref>{{cite magazine |url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=demi lovato|chart=Billboard Canadian Hot 100}} |title=Demi Lovato Album & Song Chart History – Canadian Hot 100 |magazine=Billboard |access-date=October 9, 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211121100048/https://www.billboard.com/artist/demi-lovato/chart-history/billboard-canadian-hot-100/ |archive-date=November 21, 2021 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/here-we-go-again-mw0000822778|title=Here We Go Again – Demi Lovato|first=Stephen Thomas|last=Erlewine|website=[[AllMusic]]|publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]]|location=San Carlos, California|date=July 21, 2009|access-date=June 2, 2013|archive-date=April 24, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424230751/https://www.allmusic.com/album/here-we-go-again-mw0000822778|url-status=live}}</ref> "Here We Go Again" was additionally certified Platinum in the US.<ref name="Gold & Platinum"/> The album's second and final single, "[[Remember December]]" failed to match the success of its predecessor, but peaked at number 80 on the [[UK Singles Chart]]. Lovato made her first 40-city national concert tour, Live in Concert, in support of ''Here We Go Again''.<ref name="Summer Tour 2009">{{cite web|url=http://www.aeglive.com/news/view/10206|title=Demi Lovato Announces "Summer Tour 2009" North American Headline Tour|publisher=AEG Live|access-date=January 1, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416183028/http://www.aeglive.com/news/view/10206|archive-date=April 16, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The tour, from June 21 to August 21, 2009,<ref name="LiveInConcert">{{cite web|url=http://www.artistdirect.com/nad/news/article/0,,5289041,00.html|title=Demi Lovato Lines Up Lengthy Summer Tour|date=April 16, 2009|publisher=ArtistDirect|access-date=October 5, 2013|archive-date=October 25, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025091856/http://www.artistdirect.com/nad/news/article/0,,5289041,00.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> had [[David Archuleta]],<ref name="LiveInConcert" /> [[KSM (band)|KSM]], and [[Jordan Pruitt]] as opening acts.<ref>{{cite web|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1609297/demi-lovato-to-tour-with-david-archuleta-this-summer/|title=Demi Lovato To Tour With David Archuleta This Summer|date=April 15, 2009|website=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005–present)|Viacom]]|location=New York City|access-date=October 5, 2013|archive-date=December 6, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141206030722/http://www.mtv.com/news/1609297/demi-lovato-to-tour-with-david-archuleta-this-summer/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Lovato and Archuleta received the Choice Music Tour award at the [[2009 Teen Choice Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popsugar.com/entertainment/Winners-2009-Teen-Choice-Awards-3904879|title=Announcing the Winners of the 2009 Teen Choice Awards!|website=[[Buzz Sugar]]|date=August 9, 2009|access-date=October 5, 2013|archive-date=June 30, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150630060545/http://www.popsugar.com/entertainment/Winners-2009-Teen-Choice-Awards-3904879|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato was featured alongside the [[Jonas Brothers]], [[Miley Cyrus]], and [[Selena Gomez]] on the song "[[Send It On (Disney's Friends for Change song)|Send It On]]", a [[charity record|charity single]] and the theme song for [[Disney's Friends for Change]].<ref name="pressrelease">{{cite press release|url=https://thewaltdisneycompany.com/disney-news/press-releases/2009/08/send-it-anthem-worlds-biggest-teen-stars-miley-cyrus-jonas-0|title="Send It On", an anthem by the world's biggest teen stars, Miley Cyrus, Jonas Brothers, Selena Gomez and Demi Lovato, for Disney's "Friends For Change: Project Green", will debut on Radio Disney, Disney Channel, disney.com and iTunes|date=August 6, 2009|publisher=The Walt Disney Company|access-date=October 2, 2015|archive-date=July 12, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712162256/https://thewaltdisneycompany.com/disney-news/press-releases/2009/08/send-it-anthem-worlds-biggest-teen-stars-miley-cyrus-jonas-0|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="iTunes">{{cite web|url= https://music.apple.com/us/album/send-it-on-feat-demi-lovato-jonas-brothers-hannah-montana/1445753300 |title=Send It On (feat. Demi Lovato, Jonas Brothers, Miley Cyrus & Selena Gomez) – Single |publisher=[[Apple Music]] |date=August 11, 2009 |access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130722024414/https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?id=325770503&s=143441 |archive-date=July 22, 2013 }}</ref> All proceeds from the song were donated to environmental charities supported by the Disney Worldwide Conservation Fund.<ref name="pressrelease" /> Lovato recorded "Gift of a Friend" as a soundtrack for the Disney movie ''[[Tinker Bell and the Lost Treasure]]''. The movie was released in October 2009.

In 2010, Lovato and [[Joe Jonas]] recorded "[[Make a Wave]]" as the second charity single for Disney's Friends for Change.<ref name="iTunesMakeAWave">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/make-a-wave-feat-joe-jonas-demi-lovato-ep/1445865450|title=Make a Wave (feat. Joe Jonas & Demi Lovato) – EP|publisher=Apple Music|date=March 15, 2010|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304084402/https://music.apple.com/us/album/make-a-wave-feat-joe-jonas-demi-lovato-ep/1445865450|url-status=live}}</ref> That May, Lovato guest-starred as Hayley May, a teenager with [[schizophrenia]], in the [[Grey's Anatomy (season 6)|sixth-season]] ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'' episode, "[[Shiny Happy People (Grey's Anatomy)|Shiny Happy People]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metrolyrics.com/2010-demi-lovato-stars-in-greys-anatomy-news.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100522045923/http://www.metrolyrics.com/2010-demi-lovato-stars-in-greys-anatomy-news.html|title=Demi Lovato stars in Grey's Anatomy|website=[[MetroLyrics]]|date=May 14, 2010|archive-date=May 22, 2010|access-date=March 14, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Although critics praised her versatility, they were underwhelmed by her acting and felt that her appearance was designed primarily to attract viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.entertainmentwise.com/photos/53471/1/Demi-Lovato-Stars-In-Greys-Anatomy-Pictures|title=Demi Lovato Stars In Grey's Anatomy – Pictures|first=Helen|last=Sanders|website=Entertainment Wise|date=May 14, 2010|access-date=June 2, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20131106182729/http://www.entertainmentwise.com/photos/53471/1/Demi-Lovato-Stars-In-Greys-Anatomy-Pictures|archive-date= November 6, 2013}}</ref> Later that year, she headlined her first international tour, [[Demi Lovato: Live in Concert]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/03/21/demi-lovato-announces-south-american-tour-2010/ |title=Demi Lovato Announces South American Tour 2010 |website=[[Disney Dreaming]] |publisher=[[Walt Disney Company]]|location=Burbank, California|date=March 21, 2010 |access-date=October 5, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131006170036/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/03/21/demi-lovato-announces-south-american-tour-2010/ |archive-date=October 6, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.myspace.com/demilovato/blog/531920790|title=Demi's coming to South America!! |website=[[Myspace]]|publisher=Specific Media LLC|location=Beverly Hills, California|date=March 30, 2010|access-date=March 13, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120327073542/http://www.myspace.com/demilovato/blog/531920790|archive-date=March 27, 2012}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> and joined the [[List of Jonas Brothers concert tours#Live in Concert|Jonas Brothers: Live in Concert]] tour as a guest.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.myspace.com/demilovato/blog/533484912|title=Summer tour announcement|website=[[Myspace]]|publisher= Specific Media LLC|location=Beverly Hills, California|date=April 27, 2010 |access-date=March 13, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url= https://archive.today/20120327073553/http://www.myspace.com/demilovato/blog/533484912|archive-date=March 27, 2012}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>

''[[Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam]]'', with Lovato reprising her role as Mitchie Torres, premiered on September 3, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1637866/camp-rock-2-the-final-jam-premieres-september-3-on-disney-channel/|title='Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam' Premieres September 3 On Disney Channel|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|website=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005–present)|Viacom]]|location=New York City|date=April 27, 2010|access-date=May 14, 2010|archive-date=June 13, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210613203226/http://www.mtv.com/news/1637866/camp-rock-2-the-final-jam-premieres-september-3-on-disney-channel/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam Premier Had 8 Million Viewers |url=http://www.bsckids.com/2010/09/camp-rock-2-the-final-jam-premier-had-8-million-viewers/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110827173931/http://www.bsckids.com/2010/09/camp-rock-2-the-final-jam-premier-had-8-million-viewers/|first=Sarah|last=Peel|website=BSC Kids|date=September 7, 2010|archive-date=August 27, 2011|access-date=March 14, 2010}}</ref> Critics were ambivalent about the film's plot, and it has a 40-percent approval rating
on [[Rotten Tomatoes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/camp-rock-2/|title=Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam (2010)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date=September 7, 2010|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|location=Los Angeles, California|access-date=March 13, 2013|archive-date=November 28, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121128123557/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/camp-rock-2/|url-status=live}}</ref> However, Lovato's performance was called "dependably appealing" by Jennifer Armstrong of ''Entertainment Weekly''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/article/2010/08/25/camp-rock-2-final-jam/|title=Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam|first=Jennifer|last=Armstrong|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=August 25, 2010|access-date=March 2, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304084358/https://ew.com/article/2010/08/25/camp-rock-2-final-jam/|url-status=live}}</ref> The film premiered to eight million viewers, the number-one cable television movie of the year by the number of viewers.<ref name="CR2">{{cite web|url=http://www.medialifemagazine.com/camp-rock-2-becomes-years-top-movie/|title='Camp Rock 2' becomes year's top movie|first=Toni|last=Fitzgerald|work=[[Media Life Magazine]]|publisher=Media Life Co.|location=Portland, Oregon|date=September 7, 2010|access-date=April 9, 2013|archive-date=July 25, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220725201925/http://www.medialifemagazine.com/camp-rock-2-becomes-years-top-movie/|url-status=live}}</ref> Its accompanying [[Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] was released on August 10 with Lovato singing nine songs, including "[[Can't Back Down (song)|Can't Back Down]]" and "[[Wouldn't Change a Thing (Camp Rock song)|Wouldn't Change a Thing]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/camp-rock-2-the-final-jam-music-from-the-disney/1440622360|title=Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam (Soundtrack from the Motion Picture)|publisher=Apple Music|date=August 10, 2010|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304084405/https://music.apple.com/us/album/camp-rock-2-the-final-jam-music-from-the-disney/1440622360|url-status=live}}</ref> The soundtrack debuted at number three on the ''Billboard'' 200, with first-week sales of 41,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oceanup.com/2010/08/18/camp-rock-2-soundtrack-41863-sold/|title=Camp Rock 2 Soundtrack 41,863 Sold|work=OceanUp|publisher=As If Productions|location=Los Angeles, California|access-date=April 9, 2013|archive-date=September 15, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180915193008/http://oceanup.com/2010/08/18/camp-rock-2-soundtrack-41863-sold/|url-status=live}}</ref> Jonas Brothers: Live in Concert was reworked to incorporate Lovato and the rest of the film's cast;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/04/27/jonas-brothers-2010-world-tour-camp-rock-2-tour/ |title=Jonas Brothers 2010 World Tour Camp Rock 2 Tour 20 of the show have been cancelled or moved |website=[[Disney Dreaming]]|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]] |location=Burbank, California|date=April 27, 2010 |access-date=March 13, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130816182438/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/04/27/jonas-brothers-2010-world-tour-camp-rock-2-tour/ |archive-date=August 16, 2013 }}</ref> it began on August 7, two weeks later than planned.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/07/03/jonas-brothers-cancel-camp-rock-2-tour-dates-add-others/ |title=Jonas Brothers Cancel Camp Rock 2 Tour Dates, Add Others |website=[[Disney Dreaming]] |publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]]|location=Burbank, California|date=July 3, 2010 |access-date=March 13, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120829033628/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/07/03/jonas-brothers-cancel-camp-rock-2-tour-dates-add-others/ |archive-date=August 29, 2012 }}</ref> The ''[[Sonny with a Chance (soundtrack)|Sonny with a Chance]]'' soundtrack was released on October 5; Lovato sang on four tracks, including "[[Me, Myself and Time]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/sonny-with-a-chance-soundtrack-from-the-tv-series/1443917355|title=Sonny With a Chance (Soundtrack from the TV Series)|publisher=Apple Music|date=October 5, 2010|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304084404/https://music.apple.com/us/album/sonny-with-a-chance-soundtrack-from-the-tv-series/1443917355|url-status=live}}</ref> It debuted (and peaked) at number 163 on the ''Billboard'' 200, her lowest-selling soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/sonny-with-a-chance-mw0002032615/awards|title=Sonny with a Chance – Original TV Soundtrack: Awards|website=[[AllMusic]]|publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]]|location=San Carlos, California|access-date=March 14, 2013|archive-date=January 17, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140117010709/http://www.allmusic.com/album/sonny-with-a-chance-mw0002032615/awards|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2010, Lovato announced her departure from ''Sonny with a Chance'', putting her acting career on hiatus and ending the series;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/237137/demi-lovato-quitting-sonny-with-a-chance|title=Demi Lovato Quitting Sonny With a Chance|first=Josh|last=Grossberg|date=April 19, 2011|website=[[E!]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|location=New York City|access-date=March 11, 2013|archive-date=July 16, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230716093431/https://www.eonline.com/news/237137/demi-lovato-quitting-sonny-with-a-chance|url-status=live}}</ref> she later said that she would return to acting when she felt confident doing so.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KFFkhGJ_RiY |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211221/KFFkhGJ_RiY |archive-date=December 21, 2021 |url-status=live|title=Demi Lovato – Koko Pop UK|date=April 7, 2012|publisher=[[YouTube]]|access-date=March 14, 2013}}{{cbignore}}</ref> Her departure led to the actual spin-off series ''[[So Random!]]'' with the ''Sonny'' cast, featuring sketches from the former show-within-a-show. The series was canceled after one season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tvline.com/2011/04/19/demi-lovato-exits-sonny-with-a-chance/|title=Demi Lovato Exits Disney Series: 'I Don't Think It Would Be Healthy for My Recovery{{'-}}|date=April 19, 2011|work=[[TVLine]]|location=Los Angeles, California|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130310192437/http://tvline.com/2011/04/19/demi-lovato-exits-sonny-with-a-chance/|archive-date=March 10, 2013|url-status=dead|access-date=March 14, 2013}}</ref>

===2011–2012: ''Unbroken'' and ''The X Factor''===
[[File:Demi Lovato 8, 2012.jpg|left|thumb|upright|Lovato performing on ''[[Good Morning America]]'' in July 2012 as part of the program's Summer Concert Series]]
Lovato released her third studio album, ''[[Unbroken (Demi Lovato album)|Unbroken]]'', on September 20, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1667730/demi-lovato-new-album-september/|title=Demi Lovato To Release New Album September 20|author=James Dinh|publisher=MTV News|date=July 22, 2011|access-date=March 15, 2013|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150405/http://www.mtv.com/news/1667730/demi-lovato-new-album-september/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Begun in July 2010, the album experimented with [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] and featured less pop rock than her first two albums.<ref name="Vena">{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1644100/demi-lovato-wants-to-embrace-her-inner-soul-diva-on-next-album/|title=Demi Lovato Wants To Embrace Her 'Inner Soul' Diva On Next Album|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|date=July 21, 2010|publisher=[[MTV News]]|access-date=March 15, 2013|archive-date=August 5, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210805141513/http://www.mtv.com/news/1644100/demi-lovato-wants-to-embrace-her-inner-soul-diva-on-next-album/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Lyrically, ''Unbroken'' encompassed more mature themes as opposed to Lovato's previous works, with some songs focusing on her personal struggles.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1670726/demi-lovato-unbroken-reviews/|title=Demi Lovato's Unbroken: Putting It Back Together|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|publisher=MTV News|access-date=June 24, 2019|archive-date=November 23, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171123100146/http://www.mtv.com/news/1670726/demi-lovato-unbroken-reviews/|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album and its stylistic change received mixed reviews from critics, who praised Lovato's vocals and saw a growth in her musicianship due to the songs focusing on her struggles, but criticized the album's "party songs" and found the music to be more generic than her previous efforts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/unbroken-2010/demi-lovato/critic-reviews|title=Critic Reviews for Unbroken|publisher=Metacritic|access-date=March 15, 2013|archive-date=March 22, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140322171416/http://www.metacritic.com/music/unbroken-2010/demi-lovato/critic-reviews|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Unbroken'' debuted at number four in the US, selling 97,000 copies in its first week of release; it was later certified Gold.<ref name="billboard">{{cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/tony-bennett-85-achieves-first-no-1-album-on-billboard-200-467230/ |title=Tony Bennett, 85, Achieves First No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 |magazine=Billboard |first=Tony |last=Caulfield |date=September 28, 2011 |access-date=March 4, 2022 |archive-date=March 4, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304085502/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/tony-bennett-85-achieves-first-no-1-album-on-billboard-200-467230/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

"[[Skyscraper (song)|Skyscraper]]", the lead single from ''Unbroken'', was released on July 12, and was noted for its messages of self-worth and confidence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/Demi-Lovato-Skyscraper.htm|title=Demi Lovato – "Skyscraper"|first=Bill|last=Lamb|publisher=Dotdash Meredith|access-date=June 2, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130505015245/http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/Demi-Lovato-Skyscraper.htm|archive-date=May 5, 2013}}</ref> It debuted at number ten in the US, selling 176,000 downloads during the first week of release, becoming Lovato's highest first week sales at the time.<ref name="Billboard"/> The song also became Lovato's highest-charting single since "[[This Is Me (Camp Rock song)|This Is Me]]" peaking at number nine in July 2008,<ref name="Billboard">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/lmfao-still-atop-hot-100-demi-lovato-debuts-in-top-10-469163/|title=LMFAO Still Atop Hot 100, Demi Lovato Debuts In Top 10|last=Trust|first=Gary|magazine=Billboard|date=July 20, 2011|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304085501/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/lmfao-still-atop-hot-100-demi-lovato-debuts-in-top-10-469163/|url-status=live}}</ref> and it also debuted at number two on the [[Hot Digital Songs]] chart.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/blake-sheltons-river-runs-to-no-1-on-billboard-200-469172/|title=Blake Shelton's 'River' Runs to No. 1 on Billboard 200|date=July 20, 2011|last=Caulfield|first=Kevin|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304085505/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/blake-sheltons-river-runs-to-no-1-on-billboard-200-469172/|url-status=live}}</ref> "Skyscraper" received the Best Video With a Message award at the September [[2012 MTV Video Music Awards]], and the track was also certified Platinum by the RIAA and Silver by the [[British Phonographic Industry|BPI]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/ontv/vma/2012/best-video-with-a-message/|title=Demi Lovato nominated for Best Video With A Message at the 2012 VMA's.|publisher=MTV News. Viacom|date=July 31, 2012|access-date=March 15, 2013|archive-date=May 4, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130504072100/http://www.mtv.com/ontv/vma/2012/best-video-with-a-message/|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album's second and final single, "[[Give Your Heart a Break]]", was released on January 23, 2012, and later peaked on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 at number 16, making Lovato's fourth highest-charting song to that point.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/demi-lovato/chart-history/ |title=Hot 100 Songs & New Music: 1 – 10 Songs |magazine=Billboard |access-date=December 6, 2012 |archive-date=November 21, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211121094938/https://www.billboard.com/artist/demi-lovato/chart-history/ |url-status=live }}</ref> It peaked at number 12 on the US [[Adult Pop Songs|Adult Top 40]] chart and number one on the US [[Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs)|Pop Songs]] chart. It also became the longest climb by a female artist{{Efn|Lovato identified as female at that time.|name=femalechart|group=lower-alpha}} to reach No. 1 in the [[Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs)|Pop Songs]] chart history until 2019, when [[Halsey (singer)|Halsey]]'s feature on "[[Eastside (song)|Eastside]]" broke the record.<ref name="BillboardChartHistory"/><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/benny-blanco-halsey-khalid-eastside-no-1-pop-songs/|title=Benny Blanco, Halsey & Khalid Complete Record Rise to No. 1 on Pop Songs Chart With 'Eastside'|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 4, 2022|date=February 25, 2019|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304085500/https://www.billboard.com/pro/benny-blanco-halsey-khalid-eastside-no-1-pop-songs/|url-status=live}}</ref> The song was certified triple Platinum in the US; {{as of|2014|10|lc=y}}, "Give Your Heart a Break" has sold 2.1 million digital copies.<ref name="sales">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/ask-billboard-baseball-hits-gwen-stefanis-delay-demi-lovatos/|title=Ask Billboard: Baseball Hits, Gwen Stefani's Delay & Demi Lovato's Best-Selling Songs|magazine=Billboard|date=October 12, 2014|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304085502/https://www.billboard.com/pro/ask-billboard-baseball-hits-gwen-stefanis-delay-demi-lovatos/|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Billboard'' has ranked the song as Lovato's best, calling it "timeless".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-best-songs-8238640/|title=Demi Lovato's 10 Best Songs: Critic's Picks|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=December 2, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221202044131/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-best-songs-8238640/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In May, Lovato became a judge and mentor for the [[The X Factor (American season 2)|second season]] of the [[The X Factor (U.S. TV series)|U.S. version]] of ''[[The X Factor]]'', with a reported salary of one million dollars.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zap2it.com/blogs/demi_lovatos_x_factor_salary_cant_compare_to_britney_spears-2012-05|title=Demi Lovato's 'X Factor' salary can't compare to Britney Spears'|publisher=Zap2It|date=May 30, 2012|access-date=March 7, 2013|archive-date=November 29, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129042645/http://www.zap2it.com/blogs/demi_lovatos_x_factor_salary_cant_compare_to_britney_spears-2012-05|url-status=dead}}</ref> Joining [[Britney Spears]], [[Simon Cowell]], and [[L.A. Reid]],<ref name="JoinX-Factor">{{cite web|last=Bricker|first=Tierney|title=It's Official! Demi Lovato Joins X Factor as Fourth Judge|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/315906/it-s-official-demi-lovato-joins-x-factor-as-fourth-judge|publisher=E! Online|date=May 13, 2012|access-date=May 13, 2012|archive-date=April 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230429211647/https://www.eonline.com/news/315906/it-s-official-demi-lovato-joins-x-factor-as-fourth-judge|url-status=live}}</ref> it was speculated that she was chosen to attract a younger audience.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1684289/demi-lovato-x-factor-judge-miley-cyrus/|title=Demi Lovato, Miley Cyrus Rumored For 'X Factor' Judge Spot|author=Gil Kaufman|publisher=MTV News. Viacom|date=May 2, 2012|access-date=May 16, 2012|archive-date=June 10, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220610123828/http://www.mtv.com/news/1684289/demi-lovato-x-factor-judge-miley-cyrus/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Mentoring the Young Adults category, her final act (CeCe Frey) finished sixth.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1698571/x-factor-cece-frey-elimination-reaction/|title=CeCe Frey 'Knew' She Wasn't Going To Win 'X Factor'|author=Chris Kim|publisher=MTV News|date=December 7, 2012|access-date=March 15, 2013|archive-date=June 14, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220614144558/http://www.mtv.com/news/1698571/x-factor-cece-frey-elimination-reaction/|url-status=dead}}</ref> At the Minnesota State Fair in August, Lovato announced that after a pre-show performance at the 2012 MTV Video Music Awards<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kovideo.net/demi-lovato-reveals-she-is-recording-fourth-album-soon-news-demi-lovato-6153.html |first=Irene|last=Test|title=Demi Lovato Reveals She is Recording Fourth Album Soon |work=Kovideo |publisher=Glam Entertainment |date=September 1, 2012 |access-date=March 16, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130402182638/http://www.kovideo.net/demi-lovato-reveals-she-is-recording-fourth-album-soon-news-demi-lovato-6153.html |archive-date=April 2, 2013 }}</ref> she would release a single by December.<ref>{{cite web|author=Ashley E. |url=http://www.bsckids.com/2012/08/demi-lovato-to-release-new-single-by-december/ |title=Demi Lovato To Release New Single By December |publisher=Bsckids |date=August 31, 2012 |access-date=March 16, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120905131521/http://www.bsckids.com/2012/08/demi-lovato-to-release-new-single-by-december/ |archive-date=September 5, 2012 }}</ref> On December 24, she released a video on her [[YouTube]] account of herself singing "[[Angels Among Us]]" dedicated to the victims of the [[Sandy Hook Elementary School shooting]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r8TgMkbMPkc |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211221/r8TgMkbMPkc |archive-date=December 21, 2021 |url-status=live|title=Demi Lovato – Angels Among Us |publisher=YouTube|date=December 24, 2012}}{{cbignore}}</ref> In March, she was confirmed as returning for ''The X Factor''{{'}}s [[The X Factor (American season 3)|third season]],<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-returning-for-third-season-of-x-factor-1554926/|title=Demi Lovato Returning for Third Season of 'X Factor'|magazine=Billboard|date=March 28, 2013|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032426/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-returning-for-third-season-of-x-factor-1554926/|url-status=live}}</ref> with her salary reportedly doubling.<ref>{{cite news|title=Demi Lovato Making More Money Than Paulina Rubio, Kelly Rowland In 'The X Factor'|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/demi-lovato-making-more-money-than-paulina-rubio-kelly-rowland-in-the-x-factor|publisher=Fox News|access-date=March 4, 2022|date=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615010806/http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2013/05/22/demi-lovato-making-more-money-than-paulina-rubio-and-kelly-rowland-for-x-factor/|archive-date=June 15, 2013}}</ref>

===2013–2014: ''Demi'' and ''Glee''===
[[File:Demi Lovato 2, 2013.jpg|thumb|upright|Lovato at the Redlight Traffic's Inaugural Dignity Gala in October 2013]]
Lovato's fourth studio album, ''[[Demi (album)|Demi]]'', was released on May 14, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2013/4/1/demi-lovato-releasing-new-album-demi-on-may-14.html|title=Demi Lovato Releasing New Album "Demi" on May 14|work=ABC News Radio|author=Andrea Dresdale|date=April 1, 2013|access-date=March 24, 2020|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150407/http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2013/4/1/demi-lovato-releasing-new-album-demi-on-may-14.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album features influences of [[synthpop]] and [[bubblegum pop]] and was met with generally positive reviews from music critics.<ref name="metacritic1">{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/demi/demi-lovato |title=''Demi'' Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Corporation]] |location=Chicago, Illinois |access-date=May 15, 2013 |archive-date=June 7, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130607184240/http://www.metacritic.com/music/demi/demi-lovato |url-status=live }}</ref> Although Jon Carmichael of ''[[The New York Times]]'' found Lovato's transition fun, according to ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' it signified a less mature image.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/14/arts/music/demi-lovato-and-talib-kweli-have-new-albums.html |title=New Albums by Demi Lovato and Talib Kweli |first=Jon |last=Carmichael |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=May 13, 2013 |access-date=June 1, 2013 |archive-date=August 3, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150406/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/14/arts/music/demi-lovato-and-talib-kweli-have-new-albums.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/article/2013/05/07/demi-lovatos-new-album-demi-now-streaming-online-read-ews-review-here/|title=Demi Lovato's new album 'Demi' now streaming online|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=May 7, 2013|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150406/https://ew.com/article/2013/05/07/demi-lovatos-new-album-demi-now-streaming-online-read-ews-review-here/|url-status=live}}</ref> The album debuted at number three in the US, with first-week sales of 110,000 copies, the best-selling debut week of Lovato's discography.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/vampire-weekend-debuts-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-chart/|title=Vampire Weekend Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart|author=Keith Caulfield|magazine=Billboard|date=May 22, 2013|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032429/https://www.billboard.com/pro/vampire-weekend-debuts-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-chart/|url-status=live}}</ref> It was also successful internationally, charting in the top ten in New Zealand, Spain and the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/album/34b93/Demi-Lovato-Demi|title=Demi Lovato – Demi|publisher=Ultratop. Hung Medien|access-date=June 1, 2013|archive-date=July 16, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230716231340/https://www.ultratop.be/nl/album/34b93/Demi-Lovato-Demi|url-status=live}}</ref> The album has been certified Gold in the US.<ref name="us_sales">{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=Demi+Lovato&ti=&lab=&genre=&format=Album&date_option=release&from=&to=&award=&type=&category=&adv=SEARCH#search_section|title=American album certifications – Demi Lovato – Demi|date=July 11, 2016|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]|access-date=March 18, 2017|archive-date=May 27, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230527203906/https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=Demi+Lovato&ti=&lab=&genre=&format=Album&date_option=release&from=&to=&award=&type=&category=&adv=SEARCH#search_section|url-status=live}}</ref>

The lead single from ''Demi'', "[[Heart Attack (Demi Lovato song)|Heart Attack]]", was released on February 25, and debuted at number 12 in the US, with first-week sales of 215,000 copies, the highest first week sales of Lovato's discography.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/baauers-harlem-shake-still-atop-hot-100-although-lead-shrinks/|title=Baauer's 'Harlem Shake' Still Atop Hot 100, Although Lead Shrinks|author=Gary Trust|magazine=Billboard|date=March 6, 2013|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032430/https://www.billboard.com/pro/baauers-harlem-shake-still-atop-hot-100-although-lead-shrinks/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/macklemore-ryan-lewis-top-hot-100-imagine-dragons-ariana-grande-hit-top-10/|title=Macklemore & Ryan Lewis Top Hot 100; Imagine Dragons, Ariana Grande Hit Top 10|author=Gary Trust|magazine=Billboard|date=April 3, 2013|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=January 31, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220131221338/https://www.billboard.com/pro/macklemore-ryan-lewis-top-hot-100-imagine-dragons-ariana-grande-hit-top-10/|url-status=live}}</ref> The song peaked at number ten (Lovato's third top ten entry in the US),<ref name="BillboardChartHistory" /> and was also successful in the UK, Australia, and Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/song/110bf5/Demi-Lovato-Heart-Attack|title=Demi Lovato – Heart Attack|publisher=[[Ultratop]]. Hung Medien|access-date=June 1, 2013|archive-date=July 16, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230716231327/https://www.ultratop.be/nl/song/110bf5/Demi-Lovato-Heart-Attack|url-status=live}}</ref> The second single, "[[Made in the USA (song)|Made in the USA]]" peaked at number 80 in the US.<ref name="sales" /> The third and fourth singles from ''Demi'', "[[Neon Lights (Demi Lovato song)|Neon Lights]]" and "[[Really Don't Care]]", both peaked in the top forty of the US, and at number one in the country's [[Dance Club Songs]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1823485/its-demi-lovatos-demiversary-new-single-new-lyric-video-and-performances|title=It's Demi Lovato's #Demiversary: New Single, New Lyric Video And Performances|website=[[MTV]]|publisher=[[Viacom (2005–present)|Viacom]]|location=New York City|access-date=August 3, 2014|archive-date=May 19, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220519215507/http://www.mtv.com/news/1823485/its-demi-lovatos-demiversary-new-single-new-lyric-video-and-performances/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-09-06/dance-club-play-songs|title=Hot Dance Club Songs|magazine=Billboard|date=September 6, 2014|access-date=August 28, 2014|archive-date=September 29, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929203152/http://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-09-06/dance-club-play-songs|url-status=live}}</ref> She was also certified Platinum in the US.<ref name="riaa.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA|access-date=June 1, 2019|archive-date=November 10, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201110084738/https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Lovato later released a deluxe version of ''Demi'', which included seven new tracks, consisting of four live performances and three studio recordings.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nz.news.yahoo.com/a/-/latest/25441065/demi-lovato-announces-demi-deluxe |title=Demi Lovato announces Demi – Deluxe |url-status=dead|archive-url= https://archive.today/20141107021305/https://nz.news.yahoo.com/a/-/latest/25441065/demi-lovato-announces-demi-deluxe/|archive-date=November 7, 2014|date=November 6, 2014}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> One of these songs was "[[Up (Olly Murs song)|Up]]", a collaboration with [[Olly Murs]] for his fourth studio album ''[[Never Been Better]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/music/a612094/listen-to-olly-murs-and-demi-lovatos-new-single-up/|title=Listen to Olly Murs and Demi Lovato's new single 'Up'|work=[[Digital Spy]]|access-date=March 4, 2022|date=November 24, 2014|first=Finbow|last=Katy|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150416/https://www.digitalspy.com/music/a612094/listen-to-olly-murs-and-demi-lovatos-new-single-up/|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato contributed to [[The Mortal Instruments: City of Bones (soundtrack)|''The Mortal Instruments: City of Bones'' soundtrack album]] with "[[Heart by Heart]]".<ref>{{cite web|last=Guidry |first=Ken |title='The Mortal Instruments: City Of Bones' Soundtrack Features Jessie J, Demi Lovato, Owl City & More |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2013/07/the-mortal-instruments-city-of-bones-soundtrack-features-jessie-j-demi-lovato-owl-city-more-96428/|work=[[IndieWire]] |access-date=March 4, 2022 |date=July 2, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130813083820/http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/the-mortal-instruments-city-of-bones-soundtrack-features-jessie-j-demi-lovato-owl-city-more-20130702 |archive-date=August 13, 2013 }}</ref>

On June 11, Lovato released an [[e-book]], ''Demi'', on [[Apple Books|iBooks]].<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2304349/demi-lovato-ebook/|title=Buzz Bites (5/23/13): Demi Lovato Is Releasing An E-Book!|first=Althea|last=Legaspi|date=May 23, 2013|website=[[MTV News]]|publisher=Viacom|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032426/http://www.mtv.com/news/2304349/demi-lovato-ebook/|url-status=dead}}</ref> She planned to appear in at least six episodes of the [[Glee (season 5)|fifth season]] of ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'', but only appeared in four. She played Dani, a struggling New York-based artist who befriends [[Rachel Berry]] ([[Lea Michele]]) and [[Santana Lopez]] ([[Naya Rivera]]) and interacts with fellow newcomer [[Adam Lambert]]'s character. Lovato debuted in the season's second episode, which aired on October 3, and made her final appearance in March 2014.<ref name=DemiGlee>{{cite magazine|last=Strecker|first=Erin|title=Demi Lovato headed to 'Glee'|url=https://ew.com/article/2013/08/22/demi-lovato-glee-phoebe-strole/|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=August 22, 2013|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150406/https://ew.com/article/2013/08/22/demi-lovato-glee-phoebe-strole/|url-status=live}}</ref> On November 19, she released a book, ''Staying Strong: 365 Days a Year'', which topped ''The New York Times'' bestseller list.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sugarscape.com/bookclub/news/a992770/demi-lovato-becomes-a-new-york-times-bestseller-with-book-staying-strong-365-days-a-year/ |title=Demi Lovato becomes a ''New York Times'' bestseller with book ''Staying Strong: 365 Days A Year'' |website=Sugarscape |date=September 15, 2011 |access-date=December 24, 2013 |archive-date=November 18, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161118192224/http://www.sugarscape.com/bookclub/news/a992770/demi-lovato-becomes-a-new-york-times-bestseller-with-book-staying-strong-365-days-a-year/ |url-status=live }}</ref> She then agreed to write a [[memoir]], which has yet to be released.<ref name=StayingStrong>{{cite news|last=Deutsch|first=Lindsay|title=Demi Lovato is writing an inspirational book|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/books/2013/09/09/demi-lovato-book-deal/2787867/|newspaper=[[USA Today]]|location=Mclean, Virginia|access-date=September 9, 2013|date=September 9, 2013|archive-date=September 13, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130913012005/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/books/2013/09/09/demi-lovato-book-deal/2787867/|url-status=live}}</ref> While on ''The X Factor'', her final act (Rion Paige) finished fifth.

Lovato announced her [[The Neon Lights Tour|Neon Lights Tour]] (including a Canadian leg) on September 29, 2013;<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Lipshutz|first=Jason|title=Demi Lovato Announces 2014 Tour with Little Mix, Cher Lloyd, Fifth Harmony|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-announces-2014-tour-with-little-mix-cher-lloyd-fifth-5740663/|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 4, 2022|date=September 30, 2013|archive-date=December 24, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221224192557/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-announces-2014-tour-with-little-mix-cher-lloyd-fifth-5740663/|url-status=live}}</ref> it began on February 9, 2014, and ended on May 17.<ref name="NeonLightsTour">{{cite web|last=Lovato|first=Demi|title=Neon Lights Tour|url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?v=550289248377294|publisher=Facebook|access-date=September 29, 2013|archive-date=January 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121095637/https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?v=550289248377294|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="NeonBrazilMexico">{{cite web|last=Lovato|first=Demi|title=The Neon Lights Tour comes to Brazil and Mexico|url=http://www.demilovato.com/the-neon-lights-tour-comes-to-brazil-and-mexico/|website=demilovato.com|date=October 14, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019090346/http://www.demilovato.com/the-neon-lights-tour-comes-to-brazil-and-mexico/|archive-date=October 19, 2013}}</ref> On October 21, she released her cover of "[[Let It Go (Demi Lovato song)|Let It Go]]" for the Disney film ''[[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]]'', which was released in theaters on November 27. Lovato's cover was described as more "radio friendly" and "pop" as compared to the original by [[Idina Menzel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/12/04/disney-let-it-go-frozen-lawsuit-volar-youtube-cover-views/|title=Disney Sued Over Alleged "Let It Go" Song Theft, Millions Of YouTube Covers Could Be Affected|date=December 4, 2017|website=Tubefilter|access-date=June 1, 2019|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150407/https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/12/04/disney-let-it-go-frozen-lawsuit-volar-youtube-cover-views/|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato's cover appears in the film's credits, and the song was promoted as the single for the [[Frozen (soundtrack)|film's soundtrack]].<ref name="DemiFrozen">{{cite web|last=Rubin|first=Julia Lynn|title=Demi Lovato Releases New Song 'Let It Go' From Disney's 'Frozen' Soundtrack|url=http://www.hngn.com/articles/15461/20131021/demi-lovato-releases-new-song-let-it-go-from-disneys-frozen-soundtrack-listen.htm|website=HNGN|date=October 21, 2013|access-date=October 24, 2013|archive-date=December 29, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211229162520/https://www.hngn.com/articles/15461/20131021/demi-lovato-releases-new-song-let-it-go-from-disneys-frozen-soundtrack-listen.htm|url-status=live}}</ref> The song peaked at number 38 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], spending 20 weeks on the chart. It was certified double Platinum by the RIAA.<ref name="riaa.com"/> On May 18, 2014, "[[Somebody to You]]" featuring Lovato was released as the fourth single from [[The Vamps (British band)|the Vamps]]' debut album, ''[[Meet the Vamps]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/gb/album/somebody-to-you-feat-demi/880517513|title=Somebody to You (feat. Demi Lovato) by The Vamps|publisher=Apple Music|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304081937/https://music.apple.com/gb/album/somebody-to-you-feat-demi/880517513|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On May 29, Lovato announced the [[Demi World Tour]], which marked her fourth concert tour (and first world tour, covering 25 cities) and second in support of her album ''Demi''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/546419/demi-lovato-announces-first-world-tour-dates|website=[[E!]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|location=New York City|date=May 29, 2014|access-date=May 29, 2014|first=Zach|last=Johnson|title=Demi Lovato Announces First World Tour Dates!|archive-date=January 17, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230117162939/https://www.eonline.com/news/546419/demi-lovato-announces-first-world-tour-dates|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2014, she opened the UK shows on [[Enrique Iglesias]]' [[Sex and Love|Sex and Love Tour]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a575916/enrique-iglesias-announces-uk-tour-with-demi-lovato.html |title=Enrique Iglesias announces UK tour with Demi Lovato – Music News |website=[[Digital Spy]] |date=June 6, 2014 |access-date=August 3, 2014 |archive-date=August 11, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140811182524/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a575916/enrique-iglesias-announces-uk-tour-with-demi-lovato.html |url-status=live }}</ref> and worked with longtime friend [[Nick Jonas]] on the song "Avalanche" from [[Nick Jonas (album)|his self-titled album]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7569396/nick-jonas-demi-lovato-avalanche-listen-duet|title=Nick Jonas And Demi Lovato's "Avalanche": Listen To Their Gorgeous Duet|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=November 6, 2014|access-date=November 7, 2014|archive-date=March 5, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240305125542/https://www.idolator.com/7569396/nick-jonas-demi-lovato-avalanche-listen-duet|url-status=live}}</ref> On December 24, Lovato released a music video for the song "[[Nightingale (Demi Lovato song)|Nightingale]]".<ref>{{cite web|last1=De Wilde|first1=Karen|title=Demi Lovato releases 'Nightingale' video showing Wilmer Valderrama|url=http://www.axs.com/news/demi-lovato-releases-nightingale-video-showing-wilmer-valderrama-34574|website=[[AXS (ticket merchant)|AXS]]|access-date=April 5, 2015|date=December 25, 2014|archive-date=April 6, 2015|archive-url=https://archive.today/20150406041801/http://www.axs.com/news/demi-lovato-releases-nightingale-video-showing-wilmer-valderrama-34574|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2015–2016: ''Confident''===
[[File:Demi Lovato, Future Now 2016 (Cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Lovato performing on her [[Future Now Tour]] in September 2016]]
In May 2015, ''Billboard'' revealed that Lovato was in the process of starting an "artist-centric" new record label, [[Safehouse Records]], of which she would be co-founder and co-owner. The label would be a partnership between Lovato, Nick Jonas, and her then-manager Phil McIntyre, and will form part of a new collaborative arrangement with record label [[Island Records|Island]].<ref name=island2015>{{cite web|url=http://www.islandrecords.com/artists/demi-lovato/ |title=Demi Lovato on Island Records Website |publisher=Island |access-date=December 5, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160929182014/http://www.islandrecords.com/artists/demi-lovato/ |archive-date=September 29, 2016 }}</ref> Her fifth studio album, ''[[Confident (album)|Confident]]'', was released through the new venture deal. This would be Lovato's second multi-label venture of her career; she was formerly part of Jonas Records, a UMG/Hollywood/Jonas Brothers partnership, which is now defunct.<ref name="Safehouse Records (Billboard)">{{cite magazine|last1=Halperin |first1=Shirley |title=Demi Lovato, Nick Jonas, Manager Phil McIntyre Launch Joint Venture with Island Records (Exclusive) |url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/demi-lovato-nick-jonas-manager-phil-mcintyre-launch-joint-venture-with/ |access-date=March 4, 2022 |magazine=Billboard |date=May 26, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528214542/http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/6576003/demi-lovato-nick-jonas-manager-phil-mcintyre-launch-joint-venture-with |archive-date=May 28, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Lovato released "[[Cool for the Summer]]" as the lead single from her fifth studio album, in July 1, 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Garibaldi|first1=Christina|title=YES! Demi Lovato Just Announced Her New Single 'Cool For The Summer'|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2196416/demi-lovato-cool-for-the-summer-single/|access-date=June 25, 2015|website=[[MTV News]]|publisher=Paramount|location=New York City|date=June 25, 2015|archive-date=August 2, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802155202/http://www.mtv.com/news/2196416/demi-lovato-cool-for-the-summer-single/|url-status=dead}}</ref> The song attracted attention for its [[bi-curious]] theme,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2015/07/demi-lovatos-cool-for-the-summer-is-the-anti-i-kissed-a-girl/398426/|title=Demi Lovato's 'Cool for the Summer': The Next Great Gay Anthem?|last=Kornhaber|first=Spencer|date=July 14, 2015|magazine=[[The Atlantic]]|location=Boston, Massachusetts|access-date=May 11, 2019|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150407/https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2015/07/demi-lovatos-cool-for-the-summer-is-the-anti-i-kissed-a-girl/398426/|url-status=live}}</ref> and was a commercial success, peaking at number eleven on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100,<ref>{{cite web|first=Gordon|last=Murray|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/demi-lovato-cool-for-summer-dance-club-songs-chart/|title=Demi Lovato's 'Cool for the Summer' Is Fastest No. 1 on Dance Club Songs in Two Years|magazine=Billboard|date=September 1, 2015|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032448/https://www.billboard.com/pro/demi-lovato-cool-for-summer-dance-club-songs-chart/|url-status=live}}</ref> and reached the top ten in the United Kingdom and New Zealand,<ref>Chart positions:
* {{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/5202/demi-lovato/|title=Demi Lovato|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|access-date=May 1, 2023|archive-date=July 14, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230714205034/https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/5202/demi-lovato|url-status=live}}
* {{cite web|url=https://charts.nz/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Demi+Lovato|title=Discography Demi Lovato|publisher=New Zealand Charts Portal. Hung Medien|access-date=May 1, 2023|archive-date=February 15, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180215205059/http://charts.nz/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Demi+Lovato|url-status=live}}</ref> and was certified triple-platinum by the RIAA.<ref name="riaa.com"/> On September 18, 2015, the title track "[[Confident (Demi Lovato song)|Confident]]" was released as the album's second single and peaked at number 21 on the Hot 100.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Maslow|first1=Nick|title=Demi Lovato Takes Control in Her New Song 'Confident': 'You Can't Make Me Behave'|url=https://people.com/celebrity/demi-lovato-releases-new-single-confident/|access-date=September 20, 2015|work=People|date=September 18, 2015|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150407/https://people.com/celebrity/demi-lovato-releases-new-single-confident/|url-status=live}}</ref> It topped the ''Billboard'' [[Dance Club Songs]] chart and was later certified quadruple platinum by the RIAA.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Bell |first=Sadie |date=August 18, 2023 |title=Demi Lovato Releases Anthemic Rock Version of Her Hit 'Confident' |url=https://people.com/demi-lovato-releases-confident-rock-version-revamped-7693147/ |access-date=September 17, 2024 |magazine=People}}</ref> Lovato performed as the musical guest on an episode of the [[NBC]] late-night sketch comedy ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' in October 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lewittes|first=Michael|title=Demi Lovato Performs "Cool For The Summer" And "Confident" Medley On 'SNL' – WATCH VIDEO|url=http://www.gossipcop.com/demi-lovato-snl-cool-for-the-summer-confident-video-saturday-night-live-watch-performance/|access-date=October 18, 2015|work=[[Gossip Cop]]|date=October 18, 2015|archive-date=April 5, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170405175858/http://www.gossipcop.com/demi-lovato-snl-cool-for-the-summer-confident-video-saturday-night-live-watch-performance/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Kreps|first1=Daniel|title=See Demi Lovato's Confident 'SNL' Performances|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/see-demi-lovatos-confident-snl-performances-192113/|access-date=March 4, 2022|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=October 18, 2015|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032426/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/see-demi-lovatos-confident-snl-performances-192113/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Lovato was also featured on the re-release of "[[Irresistible (Fall Out Boy song)|Irresistible]]", the fourth single from [[Fall Out Boy]]'s sixth studio album ''[[American Beauty/American Psycho]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/@falloutboy/fall-out-boy-are-smack-in-the-middle-of-leaving-the-hoth-system-in-empire-strikes-back-a6ebbdb49021|title=Fall Out Boy are smack in the middle of leaving the hoth system in empire strikes back…|author=Fall Out Boy|work=[[Medium (website)|Medium]]|publisher=A Medium Corporation|location=New York City|date=October 12, 2015|access-date=October 14, 2015|archive-date=August 2, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802050147/https://medium.com/@falloutboy/fall-out-boy-are-smack-in-the-middle-of-leaving-the-hoth-system-in-empire-strikes-back-a6ebbdb49021|url-status=live}}</ref>

Lovato's fifth album, ''[[Confident (album)|Confident]]'', was released on October 16, 2015,<ref>{{cite news|title=Demi Lovato's fifth studio album 'Confident' due out Oct. 16|url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/Music/2015/08/27/Demi-Lovatos-fifth-studio-album-Confident-due-out-Oct-16/6001440705839/|publisher=United Press International|access-date=August 27, 2015|last1=Butler|first1=Karen|date=August 26, 2015|archive-date=March 17, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210317213153/https://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/Music/2015/08/27/Demi-Lovatos-fifth-studio-album-Confident-due-out-Oct-16/6001440705839/|url-status=live}}</ref> and was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album|Best Pop Vocal Album]] at the [[59th Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Grammys 2017: The Complete Winners List|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/grammys-2017-winners-list-966483/|access-date=March 5, 2017 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=February 12, 2017|url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170310061315/https://www.grammy.com/nominees |archive-date=March 10, 2017 }}</ref> The album debuted at number two on the US ''Billboard'' 200 with first-week sales of 98,000 album units,<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/pentatonix-first-no-1-album-billboard-200-chart/|title=Pentatonix Scores First No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart|magazine=Billboard|date=October 26, 2015|access-date=March 4, 2022|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032453/https://www.billboard.com/pro/pentatonix-first-no-1-album-billboard-200-chart/|url-status=live}}</ref> and was certified Platinum by the RIAA.<ref name="Gold & Platinum"/> The album received mixed to positive reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Johnston|first1=Maura|author-link=Maura Johnston |title=Demi Lovato Lays It All Bare on 'Confident': Album Review|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/6730170/demi-confident-album-review|magazine=Billboard|access-date=October 16, 2015|archive-date=October 18, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018153115/http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/6730170/demi-confident-album-review|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Ryan|first1=Patrick|title=Album of the week: Demi Lovato|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/reviews/2015/10/16/album-review-demi-lovato-confident/73876754/|newspaper=USA Today|access-date=October 16, 2015|archive-date=October 17, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151017081857/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/reviews/2015/10/16/album-review-demi-lovato-confident/73876754/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Erlewine|first1=Stephen Thomas|author-link=Stephen Thomas Erlewine|title=''Confident'' – Demi Lovato|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/confident-mw0002876585|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|access-date=October 17, 2015|archive-date=October 18, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018201907/http://www.allmusic.com/album/confident-mw0002876585|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Reviews for Confident by Demi Lovato|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/confident/demi-lovato|website=Metacritic|access-date=October 16, 2015|archive-date=October 18, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018153109/http://www.metacritic.com/music/confident/demi-lovato|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Annie Zaleski]] from ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' stated that "''Confident'' is an impressive album by a pop star who knows what she wants—and also knows exactly how to get there."<ref>{{cite news|last1=Zaleski|first1=Annie|title=Demi Lovato comes into her own on Confident|url=http://www.avclub.com/review/demi-lovato-comes-her-own-confident-226542|newspaper=The A.V. Club|access-date=October 16, 2015|archive-date=October 18, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018153249/http://www.avclub.com/review/demi-lovato-comes-her-own-confident-226542|url-status=live}}</ref> During the album's production, Lovato commented: "I've already started recording for my new album, and I have plans to record during the tour. The sound just evolves into everything that I've been and everything that I want to become."<ref name="Lovato Exit">{{cite magazine|title=Demi Lovato Leaving 'X Factor'|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-leaving-x-factor-5840366/|magazine=Billboard|access-date=December 19, 2013|last1=Lewis|first1=Hillary|last2=Willis|first2=Cortney|date=December 19, 2013|archive-date=December 29, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211229170006/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-leaving-x-factor-5840366/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Legaspi|first=Althea|title=Buzz Bites: Demi Lovato Has Begun Recording Her Fifth Studio Album|website=[[MTV]]|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2306588/demi-lovato-fifth-album-details/|date=February 10, 2014|access-date=April 5, 2014|archive-date=January 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121095637/http://www.mtv.com/news/2306588/demi-lovato-fifth-album-details/|url-status=dead}}</ref> She further stated, "I've never been so sure of myself as an artist when it comes down to confidence, but not only personal things, but exactly what I want my sound to be and what I know I'm capable of and this album will give me the opportunity to show people what I can really do."<ref>{{cite web|last=Williott|first=Carl|title=Demi Lovato Is Already Working On Album #5|url=http://www.idolator.com/7505121/demi-lovato-tour-fifth-album|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|location=San Francisco, California|date=February 10, 2014|access-date=April 5, 2014|archive-date=March 5, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240305125528/https://www.idolator.com/7505121/demi-lovato-tour-fifth-album|url-status=live}}</ref> On October, she signed with the major modeling agency, [[Wilhelmina Models]].<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Demi Lovato Just Signed With a Major Modeling Agency|url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/demi-lovato-signed-wilhelmina-major-modeling-agency|magazine=[[Teen Vogue]]|location=New York City|access-date=October 16, 2015|last1=Lewis|first1=Casey|date=October 16, 2015|archive-date=July 16, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230716093431/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/demi-lovato-signed-wilhelmina-major-modeling-agency|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato released the music video for her R&B-infused song "[[Waitin for You]]" featuring rapper [[Sirah (rapper)|Sirah]] on October 22, 2015.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-tough-waitin-for-you-confident-video-6738435/|title=Demi Lovato Gets Tough in 'Waitin for You' Video: Watch|magazine=Billboard|date=October 23, 2015|access-date=March 4, 2022|last=Stutz|first=Colin|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032428/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-tough-waitin-for-you-confident-video-6738435/|url-status=live}}</ref> On October 26, 2015, Lovato and [[Nick Jonas]] announced that they would be touring together on the [[Future Now Tour]], to further promote ''Confident'', with shows in North America and Europe.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Strecker|first=Eric|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/nick-jonas-demi-lovato-joint-tour-6738561/|title=Nick Jonas & Demi Lovato Announce Joint Future Now Tour|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 4, 2022|date=October 26, 2015|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032446/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/nick-jonas-demi-lovato-joint-tour-6738561/|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato was honored with the first-ever [[Billboard Women in Music#Rulebreaker Award|Rulebreaker Award]] at the [[Billboard Women in Music|2015 ''Billboard'' Women in Music]] event.<ref name="Rulebreaker">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/demi-lovato-billboards-rulebreaker-women-in-music-6746374/|title=Demi Lovato to Receive Billboard's Inaugural 'Rulebreaker' Award; Will Perform at Women in Music|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 4, 2022|date=November 2, 2015|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032435/https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/demi-lovato-billboards-rulebreaker-women-in-music-6746374/|url-status=live}}</ref> On March 21, 2016, "[[Stone Cold (Demi Lovato song)|Stone Cold]]" was released as the third and final single from ''Confident''.<ref name="stonecold">Sources regarding the contemporary hit radio release of "Stone Cold":
* {{cite tweet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160406152143/https://twitter.com/gthot20/status/710156449930993664|archive-date=April 6, 2016|user=gthot20|number=710156449930993664|title=.@ddlovato's 'Stone Cold' goes to mainstream & adult top 40 radio Monday (March 21) ...<!-- ellipsis in the original -->|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=March 16, 2016|access-date=April 6, 2016}}<!--Please do not remove, because Gary Trust is Billboard's associate director of charts/radio and editor of Billboard's Chart Beat column.-->
* {{cite web|url=http://www.republicplaybook.com/track/demi-lovato-stone-cold/|title=Demi Lovato "Stone Cold"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322112204/http://www.republicplaybook.com/track/demi-lovato-stone-cold/|archive-date=March 22, 2016|access-date=March 22, 2016|work=[[Republic Records|Republic Playbook]]|publisher=[[Republic Records]]}}</ref> On July 1, 2016, Lovato released a new single titled "[[Body Say]]" to promote her tour.<ref name="bodysay">{{cite magazine|last=Iasimone|first=Ashley|title=Demi Lovato Releases Steamy New Song 'Body Say'|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-body-say-released-listen-7424023/|access-date=March 4, 2022|magazine=Billboard|date=July 2, 2016|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032442/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-body-say-released-listen-7424023/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In 2016, Lovato was honored with the [[GLAAD Vanguard Award]] at the [[27th GLAAD Media Awards]], for her support of the [[LGBT rights by country or territory|rights of the LGBT community]].<ref name="GLAAD Vanguard">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/7318828/demi-lovato-caitlyn-jenner-2016-glaad-media-awards-winners|title=Demi Lovato, Caitlyn Jenner Receive 2016 GLAAD Media Awards|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=April 4, 2016|access-date=April 5, 2016|author=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|archive-date=June 4, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604125416/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/7318828/demi-lovato-caitlyn-jenner-2016-glaad-media-awards-winners|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato was also named to ''[[Forbes]]''' [[30 Under 30]] list in the music category.<ref name="forbeslist">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/demi-lovato/?sh=370a9aba13d1|title=Demi Lovato - Musician|work=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]|language=en|access-date=November 3, 2022|archive-date=December 11, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221211124400/https://www.forbes.com/profile/demi-lovato/?sh=370a9aba13d1|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2017–2018: ''Tell Me You Love Me''===
[[File:Demi Lovato 8 (41898569045).jpg|thumb|upright|Lovato performing in [[Glasgow]] on her [[Tell Me You Love Me World Tour]] in June 2018]]
In February 2017, Lovato executive-produced a documentary, ''Beyond Silence'', which follows three individuals and their experiences with [[Mental disorder|mental illnesses]] including [[bipolar disorder]], [[schizophrenia]], [[Major depressive disorder|depression]], and [[Anxiety disorder|anxiety]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/demi-lovato-executive-produces-beyond-silence-mental-health-documentary-1201994230/|last=Ahern|first=Sarah|title=Demi Lovato on Her New Documentary: Mental Health Is 'Just as Important as Physical Health'|access-date=March 1, 2017|date=February 22, 2017|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-date=March 1, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170301182921/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/demi-lovato-executive-produces-beyond-silence-mental-health-documentary-1201994230/|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato featured in [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]]' song "[[No Promises (Cheat Codes song)|No Promises]]", released in March 2017,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Malone|first1=Dolph|title=Cheat Codes & Demi Lovato's "No Promises" Heading To Pop Radio|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2017/03/30/cheat-codes-demi-lovatos-no-promises-heading-pop-radio/|website=Headline Planet|access-date=March 31, 2017|date=March 30, 2017|archive-date=November 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106144341/https://headlineplanet.com/home/2017/03/30/cheat-codes-demi-lovatos-no-promises-heading-pop-radio/|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Jax Jones]]'s "[[Instruction (song)|Instruction]]" along with [[Stefflon Don]], released in June 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Jax Jones Has Released A Snippet Of His Demi Lovato Collab & It Has Mad Carnival Vibes|url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/demi-lovato/news/jax-jones-instruction/|work=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]]|date=June 14, 2017|access-date=June 14, 2016|archive-date=June 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625083113/http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/demi-lovato/news/jax-jones-instruction/|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2017, Lovato was included in ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine's annual list of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://time.com/4747191/time-100-john-legend-demi-lovato-gala/|title=Time 100: John Legend and Demi Lovato to Perform at Gala|first=Mahita|last=Gajanan|access-date=April 20, 2017|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|archive-date=July 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170727033852/http://time.com/4747191/time-100-john-legend-demi-lovato-gala/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://time.com/4745798/time-100-2017-full-list/|title=Time 100: How the 2017 List of Influential People Was Chosen|first=Nancy|last=Gibbs|date=April 20, 2017|access-date=April 20, 2017|magazine=Time|archive-date=October 19, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019212644/http://time.com/4745798/time-100-2017-full-list/|url-status=live}}</ref> On May 8, 2017, she announced a collaboration with sportswear line [[Fabletics]] to support the [[United Nations]]' initiative, Girl Up.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-kate-hudson-fabletics-line-girl-up-7785106/|title=Demi Lovato Teams Up With Kate Hudson's Fabletics Line to Support Girl Up|magazine=Billboard|last=Saunders|first=Nicole|date=May 8, 2017|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032436/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-kate-hudson-fabletics-line-girl-up-7785106/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In July 2017, Lovato released "[[Sorry Not Sorry (Demi Lovato song)|Sorry Not Sorry]]" as the lead single from her sixth studio album,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3024567/demi-lovato-sorry-not-sorry/|title=Demi Lovato to Release New Single 'Sorry Not Sorry' July 11|publisher=MTV News|access-date=September 22, 2017|date=July 11, 2017|first=Deepa|last=Lakshmin|archive-date=October 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005063642/http://www.mtv.com/news/3024567/demi-lovato-sorry-not-sorry/|url-status=dead}}</ref> which became her highest-charting song in New Zealand and the United States at number six<ref name="NZ">{{cite web|url=https://charts.nz/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Demi+Lovato|title=Discography Demi Lovato|publisher=New Zealand Charts|access-date=October 30, 2017|archive-date=February 15, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180215205059/http://charts.nz/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Demi+Lovato|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/post-malone-rockstar-21-savage-hot-100-camila-cabello-havana-ed-sheeran-perfect/|title=Post Malone & 21 Savage Lead Hot 100, Camila Cabello & Ed Sheeran Hit Top 10|magazine=Billboard|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=October 30, 2017|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032444/https://www.billboard.com/pro/post-malone-rockstar-21-savage-hot-100-camila-cabello-havana-ed-sheeran-perfect/|url-status=live}}</ref> as well as Australia at number eight.<ref>{{cite web|title=Taylor Swift holds #1 for second week|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/2017/taylor-swift-holds-1-for-second-week|publisher=Australian Recording Industry Association|date=September 9, 2017|access-date=October 7, 2017|archive-date=September 17, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170917034506/http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/2017/taylor-swift-holds-1-for-second-week|url-status=live}}</ref> It also became her best-selling single in the US for its 5× Platinum certification by RIAA.<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1220114014799310849|title=Demi's new certifieds in the United States: Sorry Not Sorry — 5× Platinum Confident — 2× Platinum Tell Me You Love Me — 2× Platinum Stone Cold — Platinum Confident (Album) — Platinum pic.twitter.com/Xr1jFZYpYC|author=Demi Lovato Charts|user=chartdlovato|date=January 22, 2020|access-date=January 23, 2020}}</ref> The album, titled ''[[Tell Me You Love Me (album)|Tell Me You Love Me]]'', was released on September 29 and debuted at number three on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with first-week sales of 78,000 copies.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-announces-new-album-tell-me-you-love-me-253178/|title=Demi Lovato Announces New Album 'Tell Me You Love Me'|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=August 24, 2017|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=June 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612144147/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/demi-lovato-announces-new-album-tell-me-you-love-me-w499316|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=BBdebut>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/shania-twain-now-debuts-no-1-billboard-200-albums-chart/|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|title=Shania Twain's 'Now' Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart|magazine=Billboard|date=October 8, 2017|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304081934/https://www.billboard.com/pro/shania-twain-now-debuts-no-1-billboard-200-albums-chart/|url-status=live}}</ref> It received positive reviews from music critics and became Lovato's first album to be certified Platinum in the US.<ref name="metacritic">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/tell-me-you-love-me/demi-lovato|title=Demi Lovato – Tell Me You Love Me|website=[[Metacritic]]|date=September 29, 2017|access-date=October 2, 2017|archive-date=October 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171003222538/http://www.metacritic.com/music/tell-me-you-love-me/demi-lovato|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://celebmix.com/demi-lovato-goes-platinum-with-tell-me-you-love-me/|title=Demi Lovato goes platinum with Tell Me You Love Me|date=April 8, 2018|website=CelebMix|access-date=May 11, 2019|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150409/https://celebmix.com/demi-lovato-goes-platinum-with-tell-me-you-love-me/|url-status=live}}</ref> On October 17, Lovato released ''[[Demi Lovato: Simply Complicated]]'' on [[YouTube]], a documentary focusing on her career and personal struggles.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-simply-complicated-documentary-release-date-7980778/|title=Demi Lovato Announces 'Simply Complicated' Documentary Release Date|first=Tatiana|last=Tenreyro|date=September 26, 2017|access-date=March 4, 2022|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=March 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220304081944/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-simply-complicated-documentary-release-date-7980778/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Documentary2017">{{cite news|url=http://people.com/music/demi-lovato-youtube-documentary/|title=Demi Lovato to Star in YouTube Documentary I Am: Demi Lovato|work=People|date=May 4, 2017|access-date=May 5, 2017|last=Fernandez|first=Alexia|archive-date=December 28, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171228100433/http://people.com/music/demi-lovato-youtube-documentary/|url-status=live}}</ref> It was nominated for "Best Music Documentary" at the [[2018 MTV Movie & TV Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/mtv-movie-and-tv-awards-2018-nominees-black-panther-stranger-things-1202381577/|title=MTV Movie & TV Awards: 'Black Panther', 'Stranger Things' Lead Pack In Nominations|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|date=May 3, 2018|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=May 11, 2019|archive-date=November 25, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125002905/https://deadline.com/2018/05/mtv-movie-and-tv-awards-2018-nominees-black-panther-stranger-things-1202381577/|url-status=live}}</ref> In October 2017, Lovato announced the tour dates for the North American leg of her [[Tell Me You Love Me World Tour]], with special guests [[DJ Khaled]] and [[Kehlani]]. She confirmed European and South American legs of the tour in the following months, and the tour commenced in February 2018.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Blistein|first=Jon|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/demi-lovato-plots-2018-tour-with-dj-khaled-w510328|title=Demi Lovato Plots 2018 Tour With DJ Khaled|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=October 26, 2017|access-date=October 26, 2017|archive-date=June 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180621194027/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/demi-lovato-plots-2018-tour-with-dj-khaled-w510328|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://popcrush.com/demi-lovato-tell-me-you-love-me-tour/|title=Demi Lovato's 'Tell Me You Love Me' Tour: Photos + Set List|website=[[PopCrush]]|date=February 27, 2018|access-date=February 27, 2018|archive-date=February 2, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230202141249/https://popcrush.com/demi-lovato-tell-me-you-love-me-tour/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In November 2017, Lovato released the single "[[Échame la Culpa]]" with Puerto Rican singer [[Luis Fonsi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/demi-lovato-and-luis-fonsi-drop-fiery-music-video-their-spanish-song-echame-la-culpa-watch-91243|title=Demi Lovato and Luis Fonsi Drop the Fiery Music Video For Their Spanish Song 'Echame La Culpa' – Watch!|website=[[Entertainment Tonight|Entertainment Tonight Online]]|date=November 16, 2017|publisher=[[CBS Corporation]]|location=Chicago, Illinois|access-date=November 17, 2017|archive-date=November 17, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117175945/http://www.etonline.com/demi-lovato-and-luis-fonsi-drop-fiery-music-video-their-spanish-song-echame-la-culpa-watch-91243|url-status=live}}</ref> Lovato performed at the [[March for Our Lives]] anti-gun violence rally in Washington, D.C. on March 24, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/demi-lovato-apos-performance-skyscraper-200620381.html|title=Demi Lovato's performance of "Skyscraper" at March for Our Lives will send actual chills through your body|publisher=[[Yahoo!]]|date=March 25, 2018|access-date=May 7, 2018|first=Mary Kate|last=McGrath|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150406/https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/demi-lovato-apos-performance-skyscraper-200620381.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In May, Lovato was featured on [[Christina Aguilera]]'s "[[Fall in Line]]" and [[Clean Bandit]]'s "[[Solo (Clean Bandit song)|Solo]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/christina-aguilera-and-demi-lovato-release-their-much-anticipated-collaboration-fall-in-line__22928/|title=Christina Aguilera and Demi Lovato release their much-anticipated collaboration Fall In Line|publisher=Official Charts Company|last=White|first=Jack|date=May 16, 2018|access-date=May 19, 2018|archive-date=May 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180518234646/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/christina-aguilera-and-demi-lovato-release-their-much-anticipated-collaboration-fall-in-line__22928/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Wass|first=Mike|title=Demi Lovato Lends Her Voice To Clean Bandit's Next Single, "Solo"|url=https://www.idolator.com/7679512/demi-lovato-clean-bandit-new-single-solo|access-date=May 18, 2018|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|publisher=[[SpinMedia]]|location=San Francisco, California|date=May 10, 2018|archive-date=May 27, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200527190122/https://www.idolator.com/7679512/demi-lovato-clean-bandit-new-single-solo|url-status=live}}</ref> The latter became Lovato's first number-one song in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|last=Myers|first=Justin|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/clean-bandit-and-demi-lovato-take-solo-to-number-1-we-cant-believe-it-__23225/|title=Clean Bandit and Demi Lovato take Solo to Number 1: "We can't believe it!"|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=June 22, 2018|access-date=June 22, 2018|archive-date=September 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929010720/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/clean-bandit-and-demi-lovato-take-solo-to-number-1-we-cant-believe-it-__23225/|url-status=live}}</ref> On June 21, Lovato released a new single, titled "[[Sober (Demi Lovato song)|Sober]]", which she referred to as "my truth"; it discusses struggles with addiction and sobriety.<ref>{{cite news |title=Demi Lovato sings about addiction struggles on 'Sober' |url=http://www.thenewstribune.com/entertainment/celebrities/article213598949.html |newspaper=[[The News Tribune]] |access-date=June 23, 2018 |date=June 21, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623222023/http://www.thenewstribune.com/entertainment/celebrities/article213598949.html |archive-date=June 23, 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The Tell Me You Love Me World Tour concluded the following month, having originally been scheduled to end in November 2018.<ref>{{cite news|last=Halperin|first=Shirley|url=https://variety.com/2018/music/news/demi-lovato-concert-canceled-hospital-overdose-1202883262/|title=Demi Lovato Concert Canceled Following Hospitalization for Suspected Overdose|website=Variety|date=July 24, 2018|access-date=November 15, 2021|archive-date=March 5, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240305125527/https://variety.com/2018/music/news/demi-lovato-concert-canceled-hospital-overdose-1202883262/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Murphy|first=Desiree|title=Demi Lovato Temporarily Leaves Rehab for Further Treatment in Another Facility|url=https://www.etonline.com/demi-lovato-temporarily-leaves-rehab-for-further-treatment-in-another-facility-107752|website=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|date=August 10, 2018|access-date=November 15, 2021|archive-date=March 5, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240305125554/https://www.etonline.com/demi-lovato-temporarily-leaves-rehab-for-further-treatment-in-another-facility-107752|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2019–2021: Acting return and ''Dancing with the Devil... the Art of Starting Over''===
On May 11, 2019, Lovato revealed she had signed with a new manager, [[Scooter Braun]].<ref name="variety.com">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/demi-lovato-signs-scooter-braun-manager-1203212073/|title=Demi Lovato Signs With Scooter Braun for Management|date=May 12, 2019|website=Variety|access-date=May 13, 2019|archive-date=May 12, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190512194924/https://variety.com/2019/music/news/demi-lovato-signs-scooter-braun-manager-1203212073/|url-status=live}}</ref> She shared that she "couldn't be happier, inspired and excited to begin this next chapter".<ref name="variety.com" /> In August 2019, it was revealed that Lovato would appear in ''[[Eurovision Song Contest: The Story of Fire Saga]]'', a [[Netflix]] original film, directed by [[David Dobkin (director)|David Dobkin]], based on the song competition [[Eurovision Song Contest|of the same name]]. The film was ultimately released on June 26, 2020, and starred [[Will Ferrell]] and [[Rachel McAdams]].<ref name="Billboard Eurovision">{{cite magazine|first=Ashley|last=Iasimone|url=https://www.billboard.com/culture/tv-film/demi-lovato-eurovision-will-ferrell-cast-announcement-8527879/|title=Will Ferrell Welcomes Demi Lovato to 'Eurovision' Cast|date=August 20, 2019|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032439/https://www.billboard.com/culture/tv-film/demi-lovato-eurovision-will-ferrell-cast-announcement-8527879/|url-status=live}}</ref> This marked Lovato's first acting appearance since her guest role on ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' in 2013 and her first film role since ''[[Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam]]'' (2010). Later in the month, after teasing that she had been working on a new project, Lovato revealed her return to television with a recurring guest role in the final season of the [[NBC]] sitcom ''[[Will & Grace]]'', where she played Will's surrogate.<ref name="eonline.com">{{cite web|first=Chris|last=Harnick|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1068218/demi-lovato-joins-will-and-grace-s-final-season|title=Demi Lovato Joins Will and Grace's Final Season|date=August 27, 2019|website=[[E! News]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032427/https://www.eonline.com/news/1068218/demi-lovato-joins-will-and-grace-s-final-season|url-status=live}}</ref>

In January 2020, Lovato made her first musical appearance since her hiatus with a performance of single "[[Anyone (Demi Lovato song)|Anyone]]" at the [[62nd Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Bruner|first=Raisa|date=January 27, 2020|title=Demi Lovato Brought the Audience to Its Feet In Her Grammys Return|url=https://time.com/5772107/demi-lovato-grammys/|access-date=January 27, 2020|magazine=Time|archive-date=January 27, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127064100/https://time.com/5772107/demi-lovato-grammys/|url-status=live}}</ref> The song, which was recorded four days prior to her 2018 drug overdose, was released on iTunes immediately after. On February 2, 2020, Lovato performed "[[The Star-Spangled Banner]]" at [[Super Bowl LIV]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2020/02/02/demi-lovato-super-bowl-liv-national-anthem-video-chiefs-49ers|title=Watch: Demi Lovato Sings National Anthem at Super Bowl LIV|last=Swinton|first=Elizabeth|date=February 2, 2020|magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]]|access-date=February 2, 2020|archive-date=May 13, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210513195732/https://www.si.com/nfl/2020/02/02/demi-lovato-super-bowl-liv-national-anthem-video-chiefs-49ers|url-status=live}}</ref> On March 6, Lovato released a new single titled "[[I Love Me (song)|I Love Me]]".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/06/entertainment/demi-lovato-i-love-me-music-video/index.html|title=Demi Lovato drops new single and music video for 'I Love Me'|first=Chloe|last=Melas|publisher=CNN|date=March 6, 2020|access-date=March 11, 2020|archive-date=March 7, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307081641/https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/06/entertainment/demi-lovato-i-love-me-music-video/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref> The release was supplemented by both a guest appearance and guest-host role on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]''. On April 16, she released a collaboration with [[Sam Smith]] titled "[[I'm Ready (Sam Smith and Demi Lovato song)|I'm Ready]]".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/CapitolMusicGroup/view/209098/|title=Sam Smith and Demi Lovato announce new single|website=Pressparty|access-date=April 14, 2020|archive-date=May 15, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200515085443/https://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/CapitolMusicGroup/view/209098/|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' ranked this song at number 32 on its list of The 50 Most Inspirational LGBTQ Songs of All Time.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-inspirational-lgbtq-anthems-pride-songs-1234773829/|title=The 50 Most Inspirational LGBTQ Songs of All Time|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=June 28, 2023|access-date=June 29, 2023|archive-date=June 29, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230629001056/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-inspirational-lgbtq-anthems-pride-songs-1234773829/|url-status=live}}</ref> A remix of "[[Lonely Hearts (JoJo song)|Lonely Hearts]]" by [[JoJo (singer)|JoJo]] featuring Lovato was released on August 28, 2020.<ref>{{Cite magazine|date=August 5, 2020|title=JoJo Calls to Call on Demi Lovato for Upcoming 'Lonely Hearts' Remix|first=Rania|last=Aniftos|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/jojo-demi-lovato-lonely-hearts-remix-9429906/|access-date=March 4, 2022|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032433/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/jojo-demi-lovato-lonely-hearts-remix-9429906/|url-status=live}}</ref> At the [[2020 MTV Video Music Awards]], Lovato received two nominations for her song "I Love Me", becoming the first artist in VMA history to receive a nomination every year for eight consecutive years.<ref>{{Cite magazine|date=July 30, 2020|first=Gab|last=Ginsberg|title=Ariana Grande & Lady Gaga Lead 2020 MTV VMA Nominations: See Full List|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/2020-mtv-vma-nominations-full-list-9427019/|access-date=March 4, 2022|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=May 19, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220519172850/https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/2020-mtv-vma-nominations-full-list-9427019/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet|user=mikeadamonair|number=1289624464854888448|title=#DemiLovato is now the first artist in #VMAs history to receive a nomination every year for EIGHT consecutive years, since her first nom in 2012. "I Love Me" is nominated in the 'Video for Good' category this year. pic.twitter.com/YMjpNkeAvt|date=August 1, 2020|access-date=August 11, 2020}}</ref> On September 10, Lovato released a collaboration with American DJ [[Marshmello]], titled "[[OK Not to Be OK]]", in partnership with the [[Hope For The Day]] [[suicide prevention]] movement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7914193/demi-lovato-marshmello-announce-ok-not-to-be-ok|title=Demi Lovato & Marshmello Announce "OK Not To Be OK"|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=September 8, 2020|access-date=September 9, 2020|archive-date=March 5, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240305130048/https://www.idolator.com/7914193/demi-lovato-marshmello-announce-ok-not-to-be-ok|url-status=live}}</ref> On September 30, 2020, Lovato released "[[Still Have Me]]" via Twitter; the song was later released on digital platforms.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Rowley|first=Glenn|date=September 30, 2020|title=Demi Lovato Unveils Somber Ballad 'Still Have Me' Following Max Ehrich Breakup: Listen|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-still-have-me-9457558/|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032426/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-still-have-me-9457558/|url-status=live}}</ref> On October 14, she released a political ballad titled "[[Commander in Chief (song)|Commander in Chief]]", ahead of the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 presidential election]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Melas |first=Chloe |title=Demi Lovato has a few words for President Trump |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/14/entertainment/demi-lovato-commander-in-chief-song-interview/index.html |publisher=CNN |date=October 14, 2020 |access-date=October 14, 2020 |archive-date=November 10, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211110015432/https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/14/entertainment/demi-lovato-commander-in-chief-song-interview/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref> She hosted the [[46th People's Choice Awards]] on November 15, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|date=October 27, 2020|title=Demi Lovato to Host the 2020 E! People's Choice Awards|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1202042/demi-lovato-to-host-the-2020-e-peoples-choice-awards|access-date=October 28, 2020|website=E! Online|archive-date=December 19, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219152848/https://www.eonline.com/news/1202042/demi-lovato-to-host-the-2020-e-peoples-choice-awards|url-status=live}}</ref> On November 20, she featured on American rapper [[Jeezy]]'s song "My Reputation" from his album ''[[The Recession 2]]''. On December 4, Lovato featured on a remix of the song "[[Monsters (All Time Low song)|Monsters]]" by rock band [[All Time Low]], alongside [[Blackbear (musician)|Blackbear]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Are All Time Low Teasing A Collaboration With Demi Lovato?|url=https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/are-all-time-low-teasing-a-collaboration-with-demi-lovato/|access-date=December 3, 2020|website=Kerrang!|date=December 3, 2020|archive-date=May 17, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210517160430/https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/are-all-time-low-teasing-a-collaboration-with-demi-lovato/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Lovato was chosen to perform during ''[[Celebrating America]]'', the [[primetime television]] special marking the [[inauguration of Joe Biden]]. Lovato sang "[[Lovely Day]]" by [[Bill Withers]], with appearances from President [[Joe Biden]] with his grandson.

A four-part documentary series following Lovato's life premiered on [[YouTube]] in March 2021.<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Demi Lovato to Revisit 'Darkest Point' of Her Life for 'Dancing With the Devil' Docuseries|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-youtube-originals-docuseries-dancing-with-the-devil-9510795/|access-date=March 4, 2022|magazine=Billboard|date=January 13, 2021|archive-date=April 26, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426084134/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-youtube-originals-docuseries-dancing-with-the-devil-9510795/|url-status=live}}</ref> The series, titled ''[[Demi Lovato: Dancing with the Devil]]'', was directed by Michael D. Ratner and showcased her personal and musical journey over the past three years.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Haylock|first=Zoe|date=June 25, 2020|title=A New Demi Lovato Docuseries Is Coming to YouTube to Break Us|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/06/new-demi-lovato-documentary-coming-to-youtube.html|access-date=August 2, 2020|website=[[vulture.com|Vulture]]|archive-date=April 26, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426075632/https://www.vulture.com/2020/06/new-demi-lovato-documentary-coming-to-youtube.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=White|first=Peter|date=June 25, 2020|title=YouTube Gets Back With Demi Lovato With Four-Part Documentary Series|url=https://deadline.com/2020/06/youtube-demi-lovato-documentary-series-1202969255/|access-date=August 2, 2020|website=Deadline|archive-date=November 13, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113054046/https://deadline.com/2020/06/youtube-demi-lovato-documentary-series-1202969255/|url-status=live}}</ref> It was later announced that Lovato's seventh studio album, titled ''[[Dancing with the Devil... the Art of Starting Over]]'', would be released on April 2, 2021. Lovato defined it "the non-official soundtrack to the documentary".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iheartradio.ca/news/demi-lovato-shares-new-album-details-1.14778379|first=John R.|last=Kennedy|title=Demi Lovato Shares New Album Details|publisher=iHeartRadio|date=March 16, 2021|access-date=March 16, 2021|archive-date=August 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803150409/https://www.iheartradio.ca/news/demi-lovato-shares-new-album-details-1.14778379|url-status=live}}</ref> The album features collaborations with [[Ariana Grande]], [[Noah Cyrus]] and [[Saweetie]], as well as the previously released "[[What Other People Say]]", a collaboration between Lovato and Australian singer-songwriter [[Sam Fischer]], initially released on February 4, 2021.<ref>{{cite web|last=Blakemore|first=Peyton|date=February 5, 2021|title=Demi Lovato Teams Up With Sam Fischer For New Song 'What Other People Say'|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2021-02-05-demi-lovato-teams-up-with-sam-fischer-for-new-song-what-other-people-say/|access-date=March 16, 2021|publisher=iHeartRadio|archive-date=April 26, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426082856/https://www.iheart.com/content/2021-02-05-demi-lovato-teams-up-with-sam-fischer-for-new-song-what-other-people-say/|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Dancing with the Devil... the Art of Starting Over'' debuted at number two on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with first-week sales of 74,000 album-equivalent units in the US.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/justin-bieber-justice-returns-to-number-one-billboard-200/|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|title=Justin Bieber's 'Justice' Returns to No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart|magazine=Billboard|access-date=March 4, 2022|archive-date=April 22, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230422044937/https://www.billboard.com/pro/justin-bieber-justice-returns-to-number-one-billboard-200/|url-status=live}}</ref> Prior to the release of the album, Lovato released one of the two title tracks "[[Dancing with the Devil (song)|Dancing with the Devil]]" on March 26,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/demi-lovato-releases-new-song-dancing-with-the-devil-listen/|first=Evan|last=Minsker|title=Demi Lovato Releases New Song "Dancing With the Devil": Listen|website=Pitchfork|date=March 26, 2021|access-date=March 26, 2021|archive-date=March 27, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210327132137/https://pitchfork.com/news/demi-lovato-releases-new-song-dancing-with-the-devil-listen/|url-status=live}}</ref> and "[[Met Him Last Night]]" on April 1, 2021.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-ariana-grande-met-him-last-night-interview-1150415/|title=Demi Lovato Talks Collaborating With Ariana Grande on 'Met Him Last Night'|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=April 2, 2021|access-date=April 6, 2021|archive-date=October 29, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029174416/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-ariana-grande-met-him-last-night-interview-1150415/|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Dave Audé]] remix of the song was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Remixed Recording, Non-Classical|Best Remixed Recording]] at the [[64th Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/news/2022-grammys-nominations-64th-annual-grammy-awards-announced-nov-23|title=2022 GRAMMYs Awards Show: Complete Nominations List|access-date=December 22, 2021|date=November 23, 2021|work=Grammy.com|archive-date=January 24, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220124102427/https://www.grammy.com/grammys/news/2022-grammys-nominations-64th-annual-grammy-awards-announced-nov-23|url-status=live}}</ref> On August 20, 2021, Lovato released the "[[Melon Cake]]" music video.<ref name="vulture.com">{{cite magazine |url=https://www.vulture.com/2021/08/watch-demi-lovatos-melon-cake-birthday-music-video.html |title=Demi Lovato's New Single Is a Break-Up Song for Melons |first=Rebecca |last=Alter |date=August 21, 2021 |magazine=Vulture |access-date=August 22, 2021 |archive-date=April 26, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426082855/https://www.vulture.com/2021/08/watch-demi-lovatos-melon-cake-birthday-music-video.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

Lovato launched a podcast series titled ''[[4D with Demi Lovato]]'' on May 19, 2021, with new episodes releasing every Wednesday.<ref>{{Cite web|date=March 30, 2021|title=Demi Lovato launching her own podcast|url=https://www.yardbarker.com/entertainment/articles/demi_lovato_launching_her_own_podcast/s1_13132_34501706|access-date=April 25, 2021|website=Yardbarker|archive-date=October 29, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029155908/https://www.yardbarker.com/entertainment/articles/demi_lovato_launching_her_own_podcast/s1_13132_34501706|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Demi Lovato is launching her own podcast, kicking off new TikTok series 'Headstream'|url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2021/3/30/demi-lovato-is-launching-her-own-podcast-kicking-off-new-tik.html|access-date=April 25, 2021|publisher=ABC News Radio|archive-date=April 25, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210425060426/http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2021/3/30/demi-lovato-is-launching-her-own-podcast-kicking-off-new-tik.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> Confirmed guests for the podcast include [[Chelsea Handler]], [[Jane Fonda]], [[Jameela Jamil]], [[Alok Vaid-Menon]], and [[Glennon Doyle]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-new-podcast-4d-1168532/|title=Demi Lovato to Launch New Podcast '4D'|date=May 12, 2021|access-date=May 19, 2021|magazine=Rolling Stone|first=Jon|last=Blistein|archive-date=August 23, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230823151129/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-new-podcast-4d-1168532/|url-status=live}}</ref> On July 30, 2021, a talk show hosted by Lovato titled ''[[The Demi Lovato Show]]'' was released on [[The Roku Channel]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/entertainment/the-demi-lovato-show-trailer-celebrity-guests-experts-premiere-date|title=Watch An Exclusive First Look & See The Guest List For Demi Lovato's New Talk Show|website=[[Bustle (website)|Bustle]]|first=Brad|last=Witter|date=July 21, 2021|access-date=August 2, 2021|archive-date=August 2, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802160058/https://www.bustle.com/entertainment/the-demi-lovato-show-trailer-celebrity-guests-experts-premiere-date|url-status=live}}</ref> Consisting of ten-minute episodes, it features candid, unfiltered conversations between Lovato and both expert and celebrity guests, exploring topics such as activism, body positivity, gender identity, sex, relationships, social media, and wellness.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Pedersen|first=Erik|date=February 6, 2020|title=Demi Lovato Talk Show Gets Quibi Greenlight|url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/demi-lovato-quibi-talk-show-1202852886/|access-date=January 26, 2021|website=Deadline|archive-date=April 26, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426231157/https://deadline.com/2020/02/demi-lovato-quibi-talk-show-1202852886/|url-status=live}}</ref> The show had initially been announced in February 2020 to air on [[Quibi]] under the title ''Pillow Talk with Demi Lovato'' before Quibi sold its contents to Roku.<ref>{{Cite web|date=February 6, 2020|title=Quibi Sets Demi Lovato Talk Show 'Pillow Talk With Demi Lovato'|url=https://www.thewrap.com/quibi-sets-demi-lovato-talk-show-pillow-talk-with-demi-lovato/|access-date=March 11, 2020|website=TheWrap|archive-date=April 26, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426082855/https://www.thewrap.com/quibi-sets-demi-lovato-talk-show-pillow-talk-with-demi-lovato/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Spangler|first=Todd|date=January 8, 2021|title=Roku Acquires Global Rights to 75-Plus Quibi Shows, Will Stream Them for Free|url=https://variety.com/2021/digital/news/roku-acquires-quibi-shows-free-streaming-1234881238/|access-date=January 26, 2021|website=Variety|archive-date=January 8, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108142134/https://variety.com/2021/digital/news/roku-acquires-quibi-shows-free-streaming-1234881238/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On September 17, 2021, American rapper [[G-Eazy]] released "[[Breakdown (G-Eazy song)|Breakdown]]" featuring Lovato as the second single from his album ''[[These Things Happen Too]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Mamo|first=Heran|date=September 17, 2021|title=G-Eazy & Demi Lovato Confront Their Most Harrowing Headlines in 'Breakdown' Video|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/rb-hip-hop/g-eazy-demi-lovato-breakdown-music-video-9632129/|access-date=March 4, 2022|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=February 27, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230227202936/https://www.billboard.com/music/rb-hip-hop/g-eazy-demi-lovato-breakdown-music-video-9632129/|url-status=live}}</ref> On September 30, Lovato launched a four-episode series titled ''Unidentified with Demi Lovato'' on [[Peacock (service)|Peacock]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|date=September 29, 2021|title=How to Watch 'Unidentified With Demi Lovato' Online|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/unidentified-with-demi-lovato-watch-stream-online-9638199/|access-date=March 4, 2022|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=March 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220305032457/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/unidentified-with-demi-lovato-watch-stream-online-9638199/|url-status=live}}</ref> The show follows Lovato as she searches for signs of [[extraterrestrial life]] with her sister Dallas and friend Matthew Montgomery.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Kinane|first=Ruth|date=September 27, 2021|title=Demi Lovato dishes on alien abductions and making contact on UFO docuseries ''Unidentified''|url=https://ew.com/tv/demi-lovato-unidentified-interview/|access-date=October 29, 2021|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|archive-date=September 21, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230921222426/https://ew.com/tv/demi-lovato-unidentified-interview/|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2022–present: ''Holy Fvck'' and ''Revamped''===
[[File:Demi Bogotá 20220709.jpg|thumb|upright|Lovato performing in [[Bogotá]] on her [[Holy Fvck Tour]] in September 2022]]
In early 2022, Lovato began teasing her eighth studio album, and described it as "more rock than anything".<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Rubin |first=Julia Lynn |date=May 9, 2022 |title=Living for the Moment |url=https://www.inkedmag.com/original-news/demi-lovato |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220608205324/https://www.inkedmag.com/original-news/demi-lovato |archive-date=June 8, 2022 |access-date=June 8, 2022 |magazine=[[Inked (magazine)|Inked]] }}</ref> She stated that the record is reminiscent of her debut studio album, ''[[Don't Forget]]'' (2008), and would explore "heaviness" in its sound.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Gelhoren |first=Giovana |date=April 22, 2022 |title=Demi Lovato Says They Are 'So Proud' of Forthcoming Album: 'It's My Absolute Best Yet' |url=https://people.com/music/demi-lovato-proud-of-forthcoming-album-my-absolute-best-yet/ |magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]] |access-date=May 17, 2022 |archive-date=June 7, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220607190535/https://people.com/music/demi-lovato-proud-of-forthcoming-album-my-absolute-best-yet/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Lovato further called the album her "absolute best yet" and "so representative of [her]".<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Dailey|first=Hannah|date=April 22, 2022|title=Demi Lovato Teases New Album: It's 'So Representative of Me'|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-teases-new-album-1235062445/|access-date=May 14, 2022|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=June 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220605230136/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-teases-new-album-1235062445/|url-status=live}}</ref> In February, the singer appeared on "FIIMY (Fuck It, I Miss You)", a collaboration with [[Winnetka Bowling League]]; its live rendition followed later that month.<ref name="Fiimy_RS">* {{Cite magazine |last=Mier |first=Tomás |date=February 17, 2022 |title=Demi Lovato Is 'Good' with Being Alone. But Their New Winnetka Bowling League Collab Deals With Past Heartbreak |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-matthew-koma-talk-fiimy-1292843/ |url-access=subscription |access-date=March 24, 2023 |magazine=Rolling Stone |archive-date=June 8, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220608205324/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-matthew-koma-talk-fiimy-1292843/ |url-status=live }}
* {{Cite news |last=Ferguson |first=Piper |date=February 4, 2022 |title=How Demi Lovato teamed up with Winnekta Bowling League for new duet "fiimy (f**k it i miss you)" |url=https://www.wrmf.com/how-demi-lovato-teamed-up-with-winnekta-bowling-league-for-new-duet-fiimy-fk-it-i-miss-you/ |access-date=March 24, 2023 |work=[[WRMF]] |archive-date=May 15, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230515130043/https://www.wrmf.com/how-demi-lovato-teamed-up-with-winnekta-bowling-league-for-new-duet-fiimy-fk-it-i-miss-you/ |url-status=live }}</ref> "[[Skin of My Teeth]]", the lead single from Lovato's forthcoming album, was released on June 10, 2022.<ref>* {{Cite magazine |last=Dailey |first=Hannah |title=Demi Lovato Drops 'Holy Fvck' Lead Single 'Skin of My Teeth': Stream It Now |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-skin-of-my-teeth-video-1235084633/ |magazine=Billboard |date=June 10, 2022 |access-date=August 4, 2023 |archive-date=August 4, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230804114129/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-skin-of-my-teeth-video-1235084633/ |url-status=live }}
* {{Cite web|first=Michele|last=Mendez|title=Demi's Pop-Punk Era Is Here by the "Skin of My Teeth"|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/entertainment/demi-lovato-skin-of-my-teeth-release-date-lyrics-music-video|date=May 27, 2022|access-date=May 27, 2022|website=[[Elite Daily]]|archive-date=June 5, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230605231401/https://www.elitedaily.com/entertainment/demi-lovato-skin-of-my-teeth-release-date-lyrics-music-video|url-status=live}}</ref> She premiered the song a day earlier on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]''.<ref name="BillboardFallon2022">{{Cite magazine|first=Starr|last=Bowenbank|date=June 10, 2022|title=Demi Lovato Made New Album While 'Clean & Sober': 'I'm Really, Really Proud'|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-made-new-album-while-sober-1235085489/|access-date=June 11, 2022|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=June 10, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220610171100/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-made-new-album-while-sober-1235085489/|url-status=live}}</ref> On June 6, the title of the album was officially announced as ''[[Holy Fvck]]'', along with its cover art and a trailer; it was released on August 19, 2022.<ref name="BillboardHolyFvck">{{Cite magazine|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|date=June 6, 2022|title=Demi Lovato Announces New Album 'Holy Fvck' & Release Date|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-announces-new-album-holy-fvck-release-date-1235082499/|access-date=June 6, 2022|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=June 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220606214419/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-announces-new-album-holy-fvck-release-date-1235082499/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="PitchforkHolyFvck">{{Cite web|first=Matthew|last=Strauss|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/demi-lovato-announces-new-album-holy-fvck/|title=Demi Lovato Announces New Album ''Holy Fvck''|date=June 6, 2022|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|access-date=June 6, 2022|archive-date=June 9, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220609013704/https://pitchfork.com/news/demi-lovato-announces-new-album-holy-fvck/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/demi-lovato-holy-fvck-video/|title=Demi Lovato drops 'Holy Fvck' announcement video—watch|last=Lane|first=Kwase|magazine=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|AltPress]]|date=June 6, 2022|access-date=August 4, 2023|archive-date=June 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220606200939/https://www.altpress.com/news/demi-lovato-holy-fvck-video/|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Holy Fvck'' was preceded by two other singles: "[[Substance (song)|Substance]]" and "[[29 (Demi Lovato song)|29]]", in July and August.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Zemler |first=Emily |date=July 15, 2022 |title=Demi Lovato Evokes Old School Pop-Punk in 'Substance' Music Video |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-substance-single-1383612/ |access-date=August 4, 2023 |magazine=Rolling Stone |archive-date=July 15, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220715144156/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-substance-single-1383612/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mier |first=Tomás |date=August 17, 2022 |title=Demi Lovato Alludes to 12-Year Age Gap with Ex Wilmer Valderrama on Scathing New Track '29' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-alludes-to-ex-wilmer-valderrama-relationship-29-1398290/ |archive-date=August 17, 2022 |access-date=August 4, 2023 |magazine=Rolling Stone |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220817183806/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-alludes-to-ex-wilmer-valderrama-relationship-29-1398290/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The album debuted at number seven on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with 33,000 units, becoming Lovato's eighth consecutive top-ten entry on the chart.<ref>{{Cite magazine|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/bad-bunny-encanto-tie-most-weeks-2022-number-one-billboard-200-chart-1235131892/|title=Bad Bunny Ties 'Encanto' for Most Weeks at No. 1 on Billboard 200 in 2022|magazine=Billboard|date=August 28, 2022|access-date=August 4, 2023|archive-date=August 28, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220828225234/https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/bad-bunny-encanto-tie-most-weeks-2022-number-one-billboard-200-chart-1235131892/|url-status=live}}</ref> It also topped the ''Billboard'' Top Rock Albums and Top Alternative Albums charts.<ref>{{Cite magazine|first=Kevin|last=Rutherford|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/demi-lovato-five-finger-death-punch-rock-album-charts-1235132792/|title=Demi Lovato & Five Finger Death Punch Crown Billboard's Rock Album Charts|magazine=Billboard|date=August 29, 2022|access-date=August 4, 2023|archive-date=July 16, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230716093211/https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/demi-lovato-five-finger-death-punch-rock-album-charts-1235132792/|url-status=live}}</ref> In support of the album, she embarked on the [[Holy Fvck Tour]], which commenced in [[Springfield, Illinois]] on August 13, 2022, and ended in [[Rosemont, Illinois|Rosemont]], Illinois on November 10.<ref name="HFTour">{{Cite magazine|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=June 7, 2022|title=Demi Lovato Announces Dates for Holy Fvck Fall 2022 Tour|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-dates-holy-fvck-fall-2022-tour-1235082951/|access-date=June 7, 2022|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=June 7, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220607155924/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-dates-holy-fvck-fall-2022-tour-1235082951/|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2022, a poster advertising the album and featuring Lovato in a bondage-style outfit lying on a cushioned crucifix was banned in the UK by the [[Advertising Standards Authority (United Kingdom)|Advertising Standards Authority]] for being "likely to cause serious offence to Christians".<ref>* {{Cite news |last=Meierhans |first=Jennifer |title=Demi Lovato poster banned for being offensive to Christians |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-64214750 |access-date=January 11, 2023 |work=[[BBC UK]] |date=January 11, 2023 |archive-date=January 11, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230111142319/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-64214750 |url-status=live }}
* {{Cite news |last=Kolirin |first=Lianne |title=Demi Lovato poster banned by advertising regulator for being offensive to Christians |url=https://www.cnn.com/2023/01/11/entertainment/demi-lovato-poster-banned-gbr-scli-intl/index.html |publisher=[[CNN]] |access-date=January 11, 2023 |date=January 11, 2023 |archive-date=May 22, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230522003904/https://www.cnn.com/2023/01/11/entertainment/demi-lovato-poster-banned-gbr-scli-intl/index.html |url-status=live }}
* {{Cite news |author=ASA |author-link=Advertising Standards Authority (United Kingdom) |title=Universal Music Operations Ltd |url=https://www.asa.org.uk/rulings/universal-music-operations-ltd-g22-1168872-universal-music-operations-ltd.html |access-date=January 11, 2023 |agency=[[Advertising Standards Authority (United Kingdom)|Advertising Standards Authority]] |date=January 11, 2023 |archive-date=January 17, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230117233602/https://www.asa.org.uk/rulings/universal-music-operations-ltd-g22-1168872-universal-music-operations-ltd.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

On March 3, 2023, Lovato released "[[Still Alive (Demi Lovato song)|Still Alive]]", the lead single for the [[Scream VI (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] to the slasher film ''[[Scream VI]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Brandle |first=Lars |title=Demi Lovato Unleashes 'Scream VI' Cut 'Still Alive': Stream It Now |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-scream-vi-cut-still-alive-watch-1235279108/ |magazine=Billboard |access-date=August 4, 2023 |date=March 3, 2023 |archive-date=April 1, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230401080131/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/demi-lovato-scream-vi-cut-still-alive-watch-1235279108/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The song received a nomination for the [[MTV Movie & TV Awards|MTV Movie & TV Award]] for Best Song.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/2023-mtv-movie-tv-awards-winners-list-1235323674/|title=Here Are the 2023 MTV Movie & TV Awards Winners: Full List|magazine=Billboard|last=Iasimone|first=Ashley|date=May 7, 2023|access-date=May 8, 2023|archive-date=May 8, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230508061401/https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/2023-mtv-movie-tv-awards-winners-list-1235323674/|url-status=live}}</ref> After performing a rock version of her 2013 song "[[Heart Attack (Demi Lovato song)#"Heart Attack (Rock Version)"|Heart Attack]]" on tour, Lovato officially released it with re-recorded vocals on March 24.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mier |first=Tomás |title=Demi Lovato Reimagines 'Heart Attack' as a Rock Anthem for Song's 10th Anniversary |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-releases-heart-attack-rock-version-1234702543/ |magazine=Rolling Stone |access-date=April 1, 2023 |date=March 24, 2023 |archive-date=August 21, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230821203931/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-releases-heart-attack-rock-version-1234702543/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In the following months, she continued to release rock versions of her previous hits, "[[Cool for the Summer#"Cool for the Summer (Rock Version)"|Cool for the Summer]]" and "[[Sorry Not Sorry (Demi Lovato song)#"Sorry Not Sorry (Rock Version)"|Sorry Not Sorry]]" (the latter featuring guitarist [[Slash (musician)|Slash]]), with a "darker sound backed by electric guitars and grittier lyric delivery from Lovato."<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Bowenbank |first=Starr |title=Demi Lovato Updates 'Cool For the Summer' With New Rock Version: Listen |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-cool-for-the-summer-rock-version-1235340294/ |magazine=Billboard |access-date=July 10, 2023 |archive-date=July 19, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230719233814/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-cool-for-the-summer-rock-version-1235340294/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Demi Lovato Shares 'Sorry Not Sorry (Rock Version)' Featuring Slash, Announces New Album 'Revamped'|url=https://people.com/demi-lovato-shares-sorry-not-sorry-rock-version-featuring-slash-announces-revamped-album-7561203|date=July 14, 2023|access-date=August 4, 2023|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]|archive-date=July 18, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718131149/https://people.com/demi-lovato-shares-sorry-not-sorry-rock-version-featuring-slash-announces-revamped-album-7561203|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Forbes]]'' said that re-recording her hits as "rock anthems" is a "brilliant business move," and stated that it "showcases her artistic versatility and demonstrates her willingness to evolve as an artist."<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=McIntyre |first=Hugh |title=Demi Lovato Is Re-Recording Her Hits As Rock Anthems, Which Is A Brilliant Business Move |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2023/07/07/demi-lovato-is-re-recording-her-hits-as-rock-anthems-which-is-a-brilliant-business-move/?sh=76183b163110 |magazine=[[Forbes]] |access-date=July 10, 2023 |date=July 7, 2023 |archive-date=July 10, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230710201556/https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2023/07/07/demi-lovato-is-re-recording-her-hits-as-rock-anthems-which-is-a-brilliant-business-move/?sh=76183b163110 |url-status=live }}</ref> In May, Lovato guest-starred as herself in "Met Gala", the eighth episode of the third season of comedy series ''[[Dave (TV series)|Dave]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Sepinwall |first=Alan |date=May 31, 2023 |title=How 'Dave' Landed Drake and Brad Pitt in Wild Season Three Finale |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/tv-movies/tv-movie-recaps/dave-season-3-finale-drake-brad-pitt-lil-dicky-dave-burd-rachel-mcadams-1234744472/ |magazine=Rolling Stone |access-date=November 28, 2023 |archive-date=December 24, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231224160549/https://www.rollingstone.com/tv-movies/tv-movie-recaps/dave-season-3-finale-drake-brad-pitt-lil-dicky-dave-burd-rachel-mcadams-1234744472/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On June 22, she surprise-released the song "[[Swine (Demi Lovato song)|Swine]]" as a protest song two days before the one-year anniversary of the [[Supreme Court of the United States|Supreme Court]]'s decision to overturn ''[[Roe v. Wade]]''.<ref name="swine">{{Cite magazine |last1=Paul |first1=Larisha |title=Demi Lovato Wages War to Protect Reproductive Rights on Protest Single 'Swine' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-releases-protest-song-swine-addressing-abortion-rights-1234776097/ |magazine=Rolling Stone |date=June 22, 2023 |access-date=July 10, 2023 |archive-date=July 6, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230706003807/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-releases-protest-song-swine-addressing-abortion-rights-1234776097/ |url-status=live }}</ref> A [[charity single]], Lovato's net profits from it were donated to the Demi Lovato Foundation's Reproductive Justice Fund for a year, which used the proceeds to support the nonprofits: [[NARAL Pro-Choice America]], [[Plan C]], and the [[National Network of Abortion Funds]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Denis |first=Kyle |date=June 22, 2023 |title=Demi Lovato Drops New Song 'Swine' Inspired by 1-Year Anniversary of ''Roe v. Wade'' Reversal |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/rock/demi-lovato-new-song-swine-roe-v-wade-abortion-rights-reproductive-justice-1235359732/ |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=October 13, 2023 |archive-date=July 14, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230714183539/https://www.billboard.com/music/rock/demi-lovato-new-song-swine-roe-v-wade-abortion-rights-reproductive-justice-1235359732/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On July 14, 2023, accompanying the release of the rock version of "Sorry Not Sorry", she announced her first remix album titled ''[[Revamped]]'', which features ten re-recordings of previous songs in rock format; it was released on September 15, 2023.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last1=Mier |first1=Tomás |title=Demi Lovato Will 'Reenvision' Their Pop Hits as Rock Bangers on Upcoming Album 'Revamped' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/demi-lovato-announces-revamped-album-exclusive-new-music-1234786802/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |access-date=July 14, 2023 |date=July 14, 2023 |archive-date=July 19, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230719233824/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/demi-lovato-announces-revamped-album-exclusive-new-music-1234786802/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In a press release, she said: "breathing new life into the songs that played such a huge role in my career has allowed me to feel so much closer to my music than ever before."<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Garcia |first=Thania |title=Demi Lovato's New 'Revamped' Album Will Consist of Rock Versions of Her Biggest Hits |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/news/demi-lovato-revamped-album-rock-versions-biggest-hits-1235670600/ |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=July 14, 2023 |date=July 14, 2023 |archive-date=September 20, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230920010320/https://variety.com/2023/music/news/demi-lovato-revamped-album-rock-versions-biggest-hits-1235670600/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The rock version of "[[Confident (Demi Lovato song)|Confident]]" was released as the fourth and final single in August.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Paul |first=Larisha |date=August 18, 2023 |title=Demi Lovato Is Feeling Unstoppable on 'Confident (Rock Version)' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-confident-rock-version-from-new-album-revamped-1234808886/ |magazine=Rolling Stone |access-date=August 20, 2023 |archive-date=September 20, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230920005211/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-confident-rock-version-from-new-album-revamped-1234808886/ |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Revamped'' received positive reviews from critics, who praised Lovato's vocals, the record's rock production, and new iteration of the songs.<ref name="revamped_revs">* {{Cite magazine|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/demi-lovato-revamped/|title=Demi Lovato – Revamped|last=Taylor|first=Ims|magazine=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|date=September 15, 2023|access-date=October 13, 2023|archive-date=October 2, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231002015138/https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/demi-lovato-revamped/|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite magazine |last=McClain Merrill |first=Allison |title=Demi Lovato Gives Their Hits the Rock Treatment on Revamped |url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/music/demi-lovato/demi-lovato-revamped-review |website=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]] |access-date=October 13, 2023 |date=September 19, 2023 |archive-date=October 2, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231002225810/https://www.pastemagazine.com/music/demi-lovato/demi-lovato-revamped-review |url-status=live }}
* {{Cite magazine |title=Demi Lovato Refashions Herself On 'Revamped' |url=https://www.popmatters.com/demi-lovato-revamped-review |magazine=[[PopMatters]] |access-date=September 20, 2023 |archive-date=October 2, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231002015123/https://www.popmatters.com/demi-lovato-revamped-review |url-status=live }}
* {{Cite magazine |last=Daw |first=Stephen |title=Queer Jams of the Week: New Music From Demi Lovato, K.Flay, Vagabon & More |url=https://www.billboard.com/culture/pride/queer-jams-of-the-week-demi-lovato-kflay-vagabon-1235413742/ |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=October 13, 2023 |date=September 15, 2023 |archive-date=October 2, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231002015128/https://www.billboard.com/culture/pride/queer-jams-of-the-week-demi-lovato-kflay-vagabon-1235413742/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On August 4, the fourth remix of the song "[[Eve, Psyche & the Bluebeard's Wife]]" by South Korean girl group [[Le Sserafim]] was released, which featured Lovato.<ref>{{Cite magazine |title=Le Sserafim Teams Up With Demi Lovato for 'Eve, Psyche & The Bluebeard's Wife' Remix: Stream It Now |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/le-sserafim-demi-lovato-eve-psyche-the-bluebeards-wife-remix-1235384624/ |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=August 4, 2023 |date=August 4, 2023 |archive-date=August 6, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230806200625/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/le-sserafim-demi-lovato-eve-psyche-the-bluebeards-wife-remix-1235384624/ |url-status=live }}</ref> A week after, Lovato released a cover of the song "Let Me Down Easy" from the series ''[[Daisy Jones & the Six]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Aniftos |first1=Rania |title=Demi Lovato Reimagines Daisy Jones & The Six's 'Let Me Down Easy' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-daisy-jones-and-the-six-let-me-down-easy-1235390291/ |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=August 11, 2023 |date=August 11, 2023 |archive-date=August 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230813002718/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-daisy-jones-and-the-six-let-me-down-easy-1235390291/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On August 29, Brazilian singer-songwriter [[Luísa Sonza]] released her third studio album ''[[Escândalo Íntimo]]'', which contains the Portuguese-language song "[[Penhasco2]]", a collaboration between Sonza and Lovato.<ref>{{cite web |title=Compositora que ajudou Demi Lovato a cantar em português em 'Penhasco 2' é autora de músicas da 'Rensga Hits!' |url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/the-town/2023/noticia/2023/08/31/compositora-que-ajudou-demi-lovato-a-cantar-em-portugues-em-penhasco-2-e-autora-de-musicas-da-rensga-hits.ghtml |website=Globo |access-date=August 31, 2023 |date=August 31, 2023 |language=pt |archive-date=September 22, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230922201000/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/the-town/2023/noticia/2023/08/31/compositora-que-ajudou-demi-lovato-a-cantar-em-portugues-em-penhasco-2-e-autora-de-musicas-da-rensga-hits.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> Also in August, it was revealed that Lovato was no longer represented by Scooter Braun and SB Projects, having left his management that July.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Havens |first=Lyndsey |date=August 21, 2023 |title=Demi Lovato Splits With Manager Scooter Braun |url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/demi-lovato-leaves-manager-scooter-braun-sb-projects/ |url-access=subscription |access-date=January 4, 2024 |magazine=Billboard |archive-date=January 8, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240108005143/https://www.billboard.com/pro/demi-lovato-leaves-manager-scooter-braun-sb-projects/ |url-status=live }}</ref> She signed with Brandon Creed and his Good World Management in September.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Aswad |first=Jem |date=September 8, 2023 |title=Demi Lovato Signs With Brandon Creed for Management |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/news/demi-lovato-signs-with-brandon-creed-management-1235717858/ |access-date=January 4, 2024 |magazine=Variety |archive-date=January 4, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240104085619/https://variety.com/2023/music/news/demi-lovato-signs-with-brandon-creed-management-1235717858/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On September 10, 2023, Lovato did a special performance in the "Kickoff Show" for the [[The Masked Singer (American season 10)|tenth season]] of ''[[The Masked Singer (American TV series)|The Masked Singer]]'' as "Anonymouse".<ref>{{cite magazine|title=''The Masked Singer'' season 10 premiere kickoff reveals special all-star unmasking|url=https://ew.com/tv/the-masked-singer-season-10-premiere-kickoff-reveals-demi-lovato-anonymouse/|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|date=September 11, 2023|access-date=September 15, 2023|archive-date=October 20, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231020002720/https://ew.com/tv/the-masked-singer-season-10-premiere-kickoff-reveals-demi-lovato-anonymouse/|url-status=live}}</ref> She performed a medley at the [[2023 MTV Video Music Awards]] two days later, and was chosen by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' and ''[[USA Today]]'' as one of the best performances of the show.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Lynch |first=Joe |title=2023 VMAs Performances Ranked From Worst to Best |url=https://www.billboard.com/lists/best-2023-mtv-vmas-performances-ranked/ |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=September 14, 2023 |date=September 13, 2023 |archive-date=September 14, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230914173644/https://www.billboard.com/lists/best-2023-mtv-vmas-performances-ranked/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Ruggieri |first1=Melissa |title=Brutally honest reviews of every VMAs performance, including Shakira, Maneskin and Demi Lovato |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/music/2023/09/12/vmas-2023-brutally-honest-reviews-performance-rankings/70833301007/ |newspaper=USA Today |access-date=September 14, 2023 |date=September 12, 2023 |archive-date=September 21, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230921145102/https://www.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/music/2023/09/12/vmas-2023-brutally-honest-reviews-performance-rankings/70833301007/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Lovato executive produced and hosted ''A Very Demi Holiday Special'', which featured multiple celebrity guest appearances and premiered on December 8 on [[Roku]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Bell |first=Sadie |date=October 3, 2023 |title=Demi Lovato Announces ''A Very Demi Holiday Special'' for the Roku Channel |url=https://people.com/demi-lovato-announces-very-demi-holiday-special-roku-channel-8346973 |magazine=People |access-date=October 5, 2023 |archive-date=October 20, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231020212419/https://people.com/demi-lovato-announces-very-demi-holiday-special-roku-channel-8346973 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kaplan |first=Ilana |date=December 8, 2023 |title=Demi Lovato on Her Holiday Special, Directing Documentary 'Child Star' and New Music in 2024 (Exclusive) |url=https://people.com/demi-lovato-talks-holiday-special-directing-documentary-child-star-new-music-in-2024-exclusive-8413551 |magazine=People |access-date=December 9, 2023 |archive-date=December 9, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231209145738/https://people.com/demi-lovato-talks-holiday-special-directing-documentary-child-star-new-music-in-2024-exclusive-8413551 |url-status=live}}</ref> Also in December, she made a guest appearance in the television special ''[[Dynamo (magician)|Dynamo Is Dead]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Krol |first=Charlotte |date=November 15, 2023 |title=Magician Dynamo to be 'killed' live on TV |url=https://www.nme.com/news/tv/magician-dynamo-to-be-killed-tv-stunt-show-3540007 |access-date=November 28, 2023 |website=[[NME]] |archive-date=January 18, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240118081512/https://www.nme.com/news/tv/magician-dynamo-to-be-killed-tv-stunt-show-3540007 |url-status=live }}</ref> Lovato conducted a New Year's Eve concert at the [[Cosmopolitan of Las Vegas]] in [[Paradise, Nevada]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Johnston |first=Rylee |date=October 12, 2023 |title=You Can Still Ring in 2024 With Demi Lovato: Here's Where to Buy Tickets to Her NYE Concert |url=https://www.billboard.com/culture/product-recommendations/demi-lovato-new-years-eve-concert-tickets-how-to-buy-1235440687/ |magazine=Billboard |access-date=January 1, 2024 |archive-date=January 1, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240101171533/https://www.billboard.com/culture/product-recommendations/demi-lovato-new-years-eve-concert-tickets-how-to-buy-1235440687/ |url-status=live }}</ref> She was featured on a [[blues]] cover of "[[Papa Was a Rollin' Stone|Papa Was a Rolling Stone]]" with [[Slash (musician)|Slash]], from his second solo album ''[[Orgy of the Damned]]'', released on May 17, 2024.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Grow |first=Kory |title=Demi Lovato Dives Deeper Into Rock With Slash on Temptations' 'Papa Was a Rolling Stone' Cover |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/slash-demi-lovato-papa-was-a-rolling-stone-1235022877/ |magazine=Rolling Stone |access-date=May 17, 2024 |date=May 17, 2024 |archive-date=May 17, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240517155719/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/slash-demi-lovato-papa-was-a-rolling-stone-1235022877/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Her [[Spanglish]] collaboration with [[regional Mexican]] band [[Grupo Firme]], titled "[[Chula (song)|Chula]]", was released on August 15.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mier |first=Tomás |date=August 3, 2024 |title=Demi Lovato and Grupo Firme Debut Spanglish Dance Collab, 'Chula' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/demi-lovato-grupo-firme-chula-1235073549/ |url-access=subscription |access-date=August 3, 2024 |magazine=Rolling Stone}}</ref> Lovato co-headlined the inaugural Hera HSBC festival on August 25 in Mexico City.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mier |first=Tomás |date=August 20, 2024 |title='It Was About Time': How an All-Women Fest Got Demi, Camila, and Danna to Take a Chance on Them |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/demi-lovato-camila-cabello-headline-women-artist-led-festival-hera-1235083409/ |url-access=subscription |access-date=August 26, 2024 |magazine=Rolling Stone}}</ref> Lovato starred in and made her directorial debut with ''[[Child Star (film)|Child Star]]'', a documentary film she co-directed with Nicola Marsh and co-produced under her own DLG, alongside [[OBB Media]] and [[SB Projects]].<ref name="childstardoc">{{Cite magazine |last=Rose |first=Lace |date=July 31, 2024 |title=Demi Lovato Lines Up Drew Barrymore, JoJo Siwa, More for 'Child Star' Doc (Exclusive) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/demi-lovato-jojo-siwa-drew-barrymore-child-star-hulu-doc-1235961830/ |access-date=August 3, 2024 |magazine=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> The film features Lovato's interviews with six former child stars, and "examines the high highs and low lows of growing up in the spotlight". It was released on [[Hulu]] on September 17, 2024.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Gonzalez |first=Lilian |date=September 17, 2024 |title='Child Star': How to Watch Demi Lovato's Hulu Documentary for Free |url=https://www.billboard.com/culture/product-recommendations/demi-lovato-child-star-hulu-documentary-stream-online-1235777897/ |access-date=September 17, 2024 |magazine=Billboard}}</ref> In promotion of the film, Lovato released the single "[[You'll Be OK, Kid]]" on September 13.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Zemler |first=Emily |date=September 13, 2024 |title=Demi Lovato Reassures Her Past Self on Single 'You'll Be OK, Kid' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/demi-lovato-youll-be-ok-kid-single-1235101592/ |access-date=September 17, 2024 |magazine=Rolling Stone}}</ref> 

Lovato will star alongside [[Rose Byrne]] and [[Dominic Sessa]] in the [[Stephanie Laing]]-directed ''[[Tow (film)|Tow]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Wiseman |first=Andreas |date=March 8, 2024 |title=Demi Lovato Joins Rose Byrne & 'The Holdovers' Breakout Dominic Sessa In Movie 'Tow' About Homeless Woman Caught In Tow-Company Hell |url=https://deadline.com/2024/03/demi-lovato-rose-byrne-dominic-sessa-movie-tow-1235849927/ |access-date=March 11, 2024 |magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |archive-date=March 10, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240310001601/https://deadline.com/2024/03/demi-lovato-rose-byrne-dominic-sessa-movie-tow-1235849927/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Production commenced in April 2024.<ref>{{cite web |last=Kuperinsky |first=Amy |date=April 9, 2024 |title=Dominic Sessa movie 'Tow' filming in N.J. with all-star cast |url=https://www.nj.com/entertainment/2024/04/dominic-sessa-movie-tow-filming-in-nj-with-all-star-cast.html |accessdate=April 11, 2024 |website=[[NJ.com]] |archive-date=April 26, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240426215109/https://www.nj.com/entertainment/2024/04/dominic-sessa-movie-tow-filming-in-nj-with-all-star-cast.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

